title: frypan fruitballs
directions: Heat electric frypan to 220°. Melt butter in pan; add dates and salt. Beat eggs and sugar and add to pan. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool, then add fruit and nuts. Stir in Rice Krispies and flavoring. Form 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in coconut or extra chopped nuts. Store in refrigerator. Will keep up to 1 month.

title: tadpole-in-a-hole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease sides and bottom of a baking dish. Crack the egg into the mixing bowl.
Mix.
Add undrained corn and half of the cheese to the egg.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Add the dry muffin mix.
Stir until the ingredients are wet.
(The batter will be thick.) Spoon into baking dish.
Open sausage links and pat dry.
Arrange links on top of batter.
Bake about 30 minutes until top is golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: With a rotary mixer, beat eggs to blend.
Add the salad oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating mixture until thick and foamy.
With a spoon, stir in the zucchini and the pineapple. Combine the flour with the baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture, just until blended.
Stir in mashed banana.
Divide batter equally into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: sauteed sweet vidalia onions
directions: Peel and chop Vidalias.
Melt butter in pan; saute onions until tender.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Good with meats.

title: basic sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine (butter) and sugar.
Add egg and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll out to desired thickness on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans together.
Cover with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fish gumbo
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Cook celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in fat until tender. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water. Add bouillon, tomatoes, okra and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add fish.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Remove bay leaf.
Place 1/4 cup rice in each bowl.
Fill with the fish gumbo.

title: mama's dirty rice
directions: Brown meats.
Add onions, peppers, onion tops and celery.
Add beef broth.
Simmer for all flavors to blend, about 20 minutes.
Do not let dry out.
Stir in cooked rice when ready to serve.
Meat mixture can be frozen for later use.

title: bulgoki
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and marinate for at least 1 hour.
Fry quickly in a hot skillet.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo, peanut butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with tines of fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil and add eggs. Mix well. Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture, alternate with buttermilk. Add prunes and nuts and mix well. Bake at 350 in tube pan or oblong pan 45 - 50 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing. Frost as desired.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Makes 1 pint.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Add zucchini and summer squash and cook until crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet. Add oil, chicken, garlic, basil and pepper to skillet.
Cook and stir until chicken is tender.
Combine milk and flour; add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
To serve, gently toss together chicken mixture, pasta, vegetables and Parmesan cheese.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix by hand or with fork.
Pat into greased and floured sheet cake pan.

title: cinnamon torte
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and sugar.
Work in the butter or oleo.
Beat 2 eggs and add to mixture.
It will be very stiff. Make as many thin layers (using layer cake pans) as you can.
I usually get six.
Cool.
Fill each layer with sweetened whip cream.
If you wish, you can grate sweetened chocolate over top to decorate.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cut white chocolate into small pieces in pan in prepared oven at 350°.
Turn oven off.
Add 4 or 5 pounds of Spanish peanuts. Mix well and drop on wax paper by teaspoon.
Let cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: You can substitute any fresh raw vegetables you like.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Arrange in dish and spread out.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix preserves, horseradish and dry mustard in processor, blender or with a hand mixer until well blended.
Just pour over brick of cream cheese and serve with Wheat Thins or crackers of your choice.
Yum!

title: grammie's relish
directions: Scald tomatoes for 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly together for 1/2 hour.
Seal hot in sterilized jars.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Melt chocolate over boiling water, then cool.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust and chill 2 hours or freeze.
Delicious served either way.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add Cool Whip.
Mix well again.
Freeze.
Thaw 30 minutes; cut and serve.

title: creamy barbecued pecans
directions: Blend (in large bowl) butter, salt and sauces.
Stir in pecan halves to coat.
Place pecans on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir gently every 15 minutes.
Spread cream cheese between 2 pecan halves to serve.

title: quick ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Heat until bubbly.
Add sour cream.
Stir and heat only until warmed. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until almost done.
Saute mushrooms in 1 stick of butter.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in the order listed:
soup-cream mix, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Repeat whole process until pan is filled.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°. Serves 8.

title: taco burgers
directions: Heat butter in small frypan.
Brown ground beef.
Drain fat. Add sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole with crab meat
directions: Boil broccoli.
Saute onions in butter.
Add soup and 1 can water.
Add broccoli, cheese and crab meat; mix thoroughly.
Put into casserole; sprinkle with croutons.
After baking, bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: fabulous tuna spread(no fish taste)
directions: Bring tomato soup to boil; remove from heat.
Add gelatine to cream cheese; mix until smooth.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold in tuna, onion and celery.
Pour into greased mold; refrigerate at least 1 hour, preferably overnight.
Great with crackers and good for potluck.
May use blender for celery, onions and tuna. Absolutely delicious.

title: lima bean and broccoli bake
directions: Cook vegetables separately for a few minutes.
Blend soup, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Mix with vegetables.
Add water chestnuts.
Pour into casserole.
Brown rice cereal in butter in skillet.
Pour on casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick minestrone
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Add onion and garlic.
Cook, covered, 2 1/2 minutes until onion is tender.
Remove and set aside.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Melt butter and sugar; beat eggs into mixture.
Add cut up dates.
Mix together and cook 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Mix together.
Roll into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: egg-puff tuna cakes
directions: Mix and drop by spoonful in hot oiled skillet and fry.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork mix first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moist.
Then with your hands form balls.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling into shape.
You can also freeze leftovers.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and tomatoes with water (combined with cornstarch); cook until thickened. Add beans, carrots, macaroni, onion, cheese and garlic powder. Heat. Serve with additional Parmesan cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: diabetic fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add oleo, vanilla, egg and Sweeta.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in grated apples and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 8-inch pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: doughnuts in a jiffy
directions: Heat fat to 375°.
Make a hole in center of each biscuit with thumb; stretch into doughnut shape.
Fry in fat for about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan; place on paper towels to drain.
Roll in sugar or cinnamon; serve warm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix taco seasoning, corn and beans with juice into hamburger.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix eggs, baking soda, pumpkin and vanilla together.
Put rest of ingredients in separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients a little at a time and beat on low speed with mixer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 cupcakes.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs; cream until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Divide dough into 5 parts and pat into 5 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread apple filling
on layers.
Stack layers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, syrup, brown sugar, vinegar, pepper and onion together in 1 large bowl.
Cover top with pieces of bacon.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour in oven at 375° or 400°.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crab well and add to all the other ingredients except the bread.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Serve as a spread on the rye bread.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add salt, pepper, oregano, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles, drain and mix with soup.
Layer noodles, meat.
Repeat.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple-peanut butter "sandwiches"
directions: Cut apple into thin slices and spread on peanut butter.
Top with another slice of apple. Walla! Peanut Butter-Apple "Sandwiches".

title: cranberry pancake supper
directions: Combine Bisquick, egg and milk.
Beat with a rotary beater in medium bowl until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 cup cranberry sauce (cut up).
Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles appear.
Bake other side until golden brown.

title: t. j. miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables in medium pieces.
Boil covered for 10 minutes. Turn on low heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.
Season with dry onion mix.

title: no bake blueberry cake
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 3-inch baking pan. Layer vanilla wafers on the bottom (whole wafers).
Cook the berries (no sugar added) slowly until they are just ready to burst (should still be whole and firm).
Cool.
Layer the cooled berries over the wafers.
Prepare pudding according to directions and layer the pudding over the berries.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions and layer over the pudding. Make about 3/4 cup of crushed vanilla wafer crumbs and sprinkle over the Dream Whip. Chill for 2 hours.
A cake this size will make 10 to 12 nice size servings.

title: sour cream bowknots
directions: Beat egg.
Add sifted confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Add lemon rind and sour cream.
Add sifted flour and baking powder. Mix well and knead until elastic.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 3/4 inch wide strips and diagonally every 2 inches.
Cut slit and pull through to make a bowknot.
Fry in deep fat about 10 seconds per side.
Drain, cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk well and put onto 1/2 cup flour on wax paper.
Roll dough mixture in flour until evenly coated.
Pinch off balls of dough and roll to form ball.
Pat out and place in pan with small amount of cooking oil.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add egg, shortening, water and vanilla.
Beat well.
Place in greased and floured 8-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be doubled.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Beat egg.
Add corn meal and milk.
Let stand while preparing sauce, ground beef, onion, tomato sauce, olives, corn, tomato soup, cheese and chili powder.

title: jean's fort valley beans
directions: Fry hamburger until brown; drain.
Add water, onion, salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Mix well in skillet.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot, add chicken broth, water, chicken and onion. Boil until chicken is done; then remove chicken and set aside to cool.
Flatten biscuits and cut into 6 pieces (each biscuit).
Put slices into boiling broth, stirring as you put them in so they won't stick.
Add both packs.

title: poppy seed dressing and fruit
directions: Mix first five (5) ingredients well in a mixer.
Slowly add 2 cups oil while beating.
Add poppy seed.
Makes 1 quart.
Pour about 5 to 6 tablespoons over fruit.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes and raisins in baking dish.
In heavy pan, beat eggs slightly and stir in milk, spices and margarine.
Heat slowly until margarine is melted.
Pour over bread mixture and sprinkle on 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together in a medium saucepan.
Cok on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and doughy.
Put out on wax paper.
Cool and knead.
Store dough in an airtight container.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onions in oil until lightly browned. In a soup pot, bring chicken stock to the boil. Add vegetables and simmer for 45 minutes. Dredge cheese in flour and add to soup, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Add salt, pepper, mustard, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Add beer and stir until hot. Garnish with parsley. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Put the 1/2 stick of margarine into a square baking dish or casserole and then put pan in a 350° oven to melt margarine while mixing remaining ingredients.
Beat eggs with flour.
Put the rest in and mix, then pour mixture into hot casserole dish with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle is clean.
Allow to rest about 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot cross muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in medium bowl.
Make well in center of flour mixture.
Beat together egg, oil and 2/3 cup milk. Pour into well.
Stir with wooden spoon just enough to moisten flour.
Stir in raisins. Spoon into buttered muffin tins, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake in hot 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Remove from tins.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and use as a dip or spread on crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: sand dabs
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Mix in water, vanilla and flour. Add pecans. Make into small balls. Bake in 375° preheated oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crust. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: evalee's apple bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; add to oil mixture.
Add apples and walnuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Turn into 2 oiled loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top of bread when still warm. Wrap in foil.
May refrigerate or freeze.

title: one-bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In small mixer bowl, cream butter.
Add cocoa and confectioners sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency (additional milk may be needed).
Blend in vanilla. Yields about 2 cups frosting.

title: lobster or crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Add lobster or crab, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry and drain ground beef.
Add water, chili powder, garlic salt, chilies and salsa.
Simmer uncovered 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat tortillas in microwave.
Put 1/12 beef mixture in each and roll. Place seam side down in baking pan, single layer.
Put enchilada sauce on each one.
Shred cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: souper stroganoff
directions: Dust meat in flour and pepper.
Brown in melted butter. Add mushrooms,
onion and garlic.
When meat is browned, stir in soup. Cover
and cook 1 hour.
Stir in sour cream and heat 5 minutes. Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: spicy italian cabbage
directions: Heat olive oil, add onion and celery and "sweat" for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Stir; add herbs, spices, garlic and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, parsley and stir in well.
Add diced cabbage, cover lightly and cook for 20 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Remove from heat, add salt and pepper, Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Place in casserole and bake for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with extra Parmesan cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, cooking oil and carrots together and add to dry ingredients.
Beat hard.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: picadillo(ernest hemingway's recipe, finca vigia, cuba)
directions: Soak raisins in hot broth for 10 minutes or until plump. Drain.
Heat oil in large skillet and quickly brown beef, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add wine, onion, salt, garlic, oregano, cloves and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in almonds and raisins.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.
Omit salt if wanted.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Mix all together; let set in refrigerator awhile. Spread on muffins; place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice very thin.
Salt lightly and let stand 1 hour.

title: trash
directions: Mix and melt last 3 ingredients and pour over cereal.
Cool completely.
Pour 1 box powdered sugar into plastic bag; put in cereal and shake until blended.

title: fruit magic
directions: Put can of fruit in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Dot with oleo.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: karen's quick-n-good peach cobbler
directions: Filling: In saucepan, add pie filling, 1 cup of sugar and 1 stick margarine. Cook on medium-low until well blended. Set aside.

title: artichoke aspic
directions: Heat Clamato juice to boiling.
Dissolve gelatine in juice. Add drained artichokes and seasonings and chill in a mold.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Cook vegetables in salted water for a few minutes and drain.
In a casserole, layer hamburger, vegetables and spread soup over evenly.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover for last ten minutes of cooking.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Add oregano and garlic.
Grease a baking sheet.
Flatten biscuits to 4-inch circles with floured custard cup.
Fill with tomato paste and sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toast English muffins (after you halve them).
Spread with mixture, then quarter.
Broil for 10 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken "leftover" casserole
directions: Use a two-quart or larger casserole dish.
Put one half of the gravy on the bottom, then layer the stuffing, the meat and then potatoes.
Put the remaining gravy over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and mix with peanut butter.
Stir in confectioners sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla, form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Stick a toothpick into each one. Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours, or in freezer 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler or microwave, then dip each ball in mixture, remove toothpick and chill.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put meat into crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion and drain off fat.
Put bacon and onion and remaining ingredients into the crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 9 hours.

title: creamy ranch pork chops and rice
directions: Cook pork chops in skillet with oil until brown.
Add soup, milk and 1/2 package Ranch mix.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat and cover.
Cook over low heat until done.
Add remaining half of Ranch mix to water with rice for a side dish.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat until smooth. Add enough whole milk to reach "fill line" on freezer. Makes one gallon.

title: lasagna
directions: In saucepan, fry hamburger, pepper and onion together; drain. Mix mushrooms, sauce and hamburger mixture together.
Put a thin layer of sauce mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then layer of noodles, layer of sauce, layer of cottage cheese, layer of Parmesan and layer of Mozzarella.
Start all over again with noodles, then sauce, cottage cheese, Parmesan and ending with Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until the cheese is lightly browned.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes after cooking, then serve.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Put drained tuna, milk and soup into casserole dish.
Smash chips in bag and then pour over soup and tuna mixture.
Mix together with a spoon.
Bake, uncovered, until browned, about 40 minutes, at 350°.

title: quesadillas
directions: Make beef or chicken filling according to package directions. In hot skillet, lightly oiled, brown a tortilla shell on one side only.
Sprinkle cheese over shell.
Add meat, tomatoes, onion, lettuce and black olives.
Fold shell in half and wait a few moments.
Remove from pan and cut in half.
Place on a plate, place a teaspoon of sour cream on each half.
Garnish with fresh parsley and fresh fruit.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15-20 minutes.
Drain and serve.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mexican soup
directions: Saute chopped onion with hamburger meat.
Drain grease from meat.
Add all ingredients into pot; bring to a boil, cover and let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
May add water if more juice is desired.
Good with cornbread, crackers or Cheddar cheese.

title: birdfeeder
directions: Attach the string by tying a knot to the pine cone stem.
With a knife, spread the peanut butter all over the pine cone.
Place the birdseed in a pie tin.
Roll the pine cones in the birdseed until covered.
Hang the pine cones high on a tree out of reach of any cats.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and Choco-Bake.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and baking powder.
Add eggs and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in raspberries and ice cream.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve topped with Cool Whip and garnished with fresh raspberries.

title: kentucky chili
directions: Saute pepper and onion in skillet.
Brown ground beef also. In saucepan, mix kidney beans, crushed tomatoes and a dash of cumin, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add ground beef, pepper and onion into saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Pour dressing over stew meat.
Cook on low in crock-pot all day while at work.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or on a bun.

title: doritos salad
directions: Fry hamburger; drain and let cool.
Chop lettuce into bite size pieces.
Chop tomatoes, avocado and green onions.
Grate cheese.
Add all other ingredients, except the hamburger and Doritos, to lettuce.
Just before serving, add hamburger and Doritos, slightly crushed, to salad mixture.
Use the Good Seasons salad dressing, prepared by directions on package.
Toss.

directions: Heat oven to

Add onion, green pepper,

or until tender.
Add broccoli, butter and rest of ingredients,

or bread crumbs.
Simmer in oven, uncovered, until
