Serve
over toasted rolls or noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat water and Cheez Whiz until cheese melts.
Add other ingredients.
Heat until melted.
Pour into buttered 13 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 300° until brown on top.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into glass jar.

Shake well before using, or put all ingredients into blender and process on high speed until all ingredients are integrated into a smooth creamy dressing that does not separate, then put it into a glass jar.
It's very tasty and economical.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Heat oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and milk in a medium bowl. In a deep pan, heat oil on high.
Dip tomato slices, one at a time, into batter.
Fry quickly, turning once with tongs. Remove from oil and stand up, like a wheel, to drain and avoid becoming soggy before serving.

title: cheese snack bread
directions: Thaw and raise bread according to directions.
When risen, spread in a square 8-inch pan that has been greased.
Grate cheese.
Combine egg, onion, salt and milk.
Add cheese and spread over bread dough.
Sprinkle with caraway or poppy seed.
(I usually do half and half.)
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Excellent served warm with soup.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with peanut butter and sugar.
Roll into small balls.
Freeze balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Add and combine butter and cheese.
Pour over macaroni, mix well.
Add salt, pepper, eggs and milk; mix well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with thickened stewed tomatoes.

title: cajun potato fritters
directions: Bake all potatoes until soft.
In large bowl, mash peeled potatoes with parsley, bacon, garlic, green onions, nutmeg and Cheddar.
Mix well.
From mixture make small patties about the size of a biscuit and 1/2 to 3/4-inches thick.

title: tuna-potato chip casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add onion; bring to a boil while stirring.
Season (salt and pepper).
Place 1/2 of potato chips in casserole with 1/2 of tuna.
Repeat layers.
Pour mushroom soup over all; garnish with whole chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin stuff
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup melted butter in bowl.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: tennessee pride country kitchen casserole
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until browned.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
Spread croutons on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover croutons with cheeses.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and onion over cheeses.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, cream, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in lukewarm water; let it get cold.
Melt grease, but do not have it warm.
Mix cool oil, Borax and ammonia in grease, stirring well, then slowly drain the lye into mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir mixture until it is about as thick as honey (about 10 minutes).
If stirred too long, it will be grainy. Pour into flat pan or box to harden.
When hard, cut into blocks.

title: barbecue baked liver
directions: Wash liver.
Coat with flour.
Place in nonstick roaster. Place onion over liver.
Lay bacon slices on top.
Pour 1/2 of barbecue sauce over liver.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Turn liver and pour remaining sauce over liver.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 30 (2-inch) muffin cups with foil baking cups or place foil-liners on baking sheets.
Combine brownie mix, fudge packet from mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.

title: recipe for living
directions: In a crust or casserole dish, layer onions, zucchini and tomatoes in 2 to 3 layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, carrot, sour cream and soup.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Line a dish with part of stuffing.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing in dish.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing over the top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter, then add eggs, one at a time, breaking the whole egg into the batter and beating hard.
Add alternately 3 cups flour, then take the remaining 2 cups flour and add spices to it and sift 2 or 3 times.
Dredge fruit with this, adding that last to your cake. This makes 2 large cakes.

title: peach pie (cobbler)
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Make a batter of the sugar, flour and milk.
When mixed, pour over the melted butter, but do not stir.
Last, empty the peaches over the batter.
Bake in a 375° oven about 40 minutes.
Whipped cream or ice cream may be served with this.
Blackberries may be used also.

title: roast chicken with lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken inside and out; pat dry. Season inside and out with salt and pepper.
Rub garlic over the skin, then place inside cavity.
Stuff lemon and onion inside cavity.
Tie legs together.

title: pineapple upside-down rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the scalded milk, 1/2 cup Crisco, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Stir in yeast mixture, eggs and flour.
Let rise until doubled; stir down.
Cream together 1/2 cup Crisco and brown sugar.
Put a teaspoon of the creamed mixture into each greased muffin cup.
Place 1/4 of a maraschino cherry in the center and then add a teaspoon of crushed pineapple.
Spoon roll dough onto top of creamed mixture in each muffin cup until each is 3/4 full.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Invert muffin pans onto cookie sheets immediately after removing from the oven.
Allow a few minutes for the topping to run down the sides of the rolls and then remove the pan.
Yields 3 dozen muffins.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Fry and drain bacon.
Break into pieces.
Fry onion with hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together in a large baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: apple orange cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and shape into cookies. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 18 cookies.

title: heloise's pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Cook for about 5 minutes over high heat or to 210° on a candy thermometer.
Stir often, scraping the bottom of the pan well.
The mixture will foam up.
Add butter or oleo and pecans. Continue cooking over medium heat.
Stir constantly, scraping sides and bottom of pan until candy reaches softball stage (234°). Remove from heat.
Cool slightly, about 2 minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop by tablespoon onto a sheet of waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Cool completely before serving.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together oleo and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar. Add milk and pudding.
Beat all together with cream cheese and oleo mixture.
In another bowl, crush Oreo cookies.
Layer white mixture, then Oreos; last layer should be Oreos.
Add gummy worms. Refrigerate before serving.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk in bowl at lowest speed of rotary beater until blended, about 30 seconds.
Blend in pumpkin, spice, and 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill 4 hours.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and pecans.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, oil, salt, soda, cinnamon and eggs.
Mix apples, nuts and raisins.
Put into a greased 11 x 14-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 more minutes.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: iced cherry soup
directions: Drain cherries; save juice.
Add water to cherry juice to make 5 cups.
Over medium heat, heat cherries, liquid, sugar, lemon juice and anise seed to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Using a blender, blend mixture until smooth, 1/2 mixture at a time.
Then heat mixture to boil again.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: Boil fryer and bone.
Cut into pieces.
Spread chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix soups and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Spread stuffing mix over top of chicken and pour chicken broth over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Easy and freezes well.

title: southwestern chicken salad spirals
directions: Stir together chicken and next 7 ingredients. Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Stir in pine nuts, if desired. Spoon evenly over tortillas and roll up. Cut each roll into 5 slices, securing with wooden picks if necessary. Yields 40 appetizers.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt with the cold milk.
Add scalded milk while stirring constantly.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook two minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut.
Mix well; cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Cool until ready to serve, then whip egg whites until stiff.
Spread on pie and bake in hot (425°) oven until light brown, approximately 5 minutes.

title: taco dinner
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat, then add taco seasoning, refried beans, picante sauce and chilies.
Stir ingredients well and heat.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with sour cream, then sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 minutes.
Serve hot with lettuce, tomatoes, corn chips or flour tortillas.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Chop peppers.
Add garlic and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and margarine; add powdered sugar.
Prepare pudding with milk and combine with cream mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Line flowerpot with aluminum foil, layer cookies and cream mixture, ending with cookies.

title: sugar-free banana nut bread
directions: Sift together in large bowl flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add shortening or margarine and eggs, nuts and mashed bananas.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Check doneness with toothpick.
Don't overbake.
Makes 2 nice loaves.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute shrimp, crab meat and butter in saucepan.
Mix milk, cheese, peppers and onion in blender.
Mix corn meal, salt, baking powder, corn and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add cheese mixture. Add shrimp and crab meat.
Bake in long baking pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together.
Form in mound on serving chip and dip platter.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced onions and chopped tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Excellent for parties.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients in bowl for 3 minutes by hand. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar; let cool.
Add fruit juice; chill.
Add a small amount of green food coloring. Add ice water and ginger ale.
Serve.

title: barbecued beef on buns
directions: Cut cooked beef into small pieces and brown very lightly with the chopped onions in shortening or oil.
Pour off drippings. Combine beef broth or bouillon with remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring to blend and simmer 5 minutes.
Add meat to onion mixture and simmer 30 minutes or longer.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Serve on warm buns.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease bottom of an 8 x 11-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan with margarine or Pam.
Mix milk, sugar and pudding mix together. Slowly add Cool Whip to mix.
Layer bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Layer again with crackers.
Pour remaining mixture over crackers.
Cover top with crackers, covering top well so icing will go to the edges of pan. Refrigerate 2 hours (important).
Cover completely with chocolate frosting.
Chill several hours before cutting.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in cooker.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Lower temperature and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add flour, water, vanilla and nuts; chill.
Roll in individual balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes;
cool.

title: make a dream pie
directions: Combine whipped topping mix with 1 cup of milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high 6 minutes or until peaks form. Add remaining milk and pie filling.
Blend on low.
Beat on high 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: coconut crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl until dough forms.
Shape into 2 inch crescents and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until golden, about 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Can be prepared and stored in airtight container for up to a week.

title: scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut in butter and currants.
Add milk to make soft.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead half a dozen times; cut dough in half.
Roll out each half of the dough in 3/4-inch high rounds.
Cut with knife before baking.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: jennifer's blowing bubbles
directions: Mix equal parts baby shampoo with water.
Bubble blowing wands can be made from pipe cleaners.
Add either glycerin or sugar and the bubbles will last longer.
Put about 2 inches in a cup, give to a child and let them blow.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off excess fat.
Add beans, tomatoes and soup.
Layer in a large casserole dish.
First, tortillas, then meat mixture and cheese.
Do at least 3 more layers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: cranberry slush punch
directions: In a bowl, combine the cranberry sauce, concentrate, water, cinnamon and allspice. Cover and freeze for 8 hours or overnight. Remove from the freezer 45 minutes before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare banana pudding using 4 cups of milk as directed on the box.
Mix well.
Gradually add Cool Whip until blended.
Add sugar and mix for about 1 minute.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer first vanilla wafers, bananas (sliced thin), pudding and finished layers with pudding.
Garnish with remaining wafers.
Refrigerate for about 8 hours before serving.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese, Worcestershire, lemon juice, mayonnaise, onion and garlic salt.
Press into a 9 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix chili sauce and horseradish; spread onto mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle crabmeat on top.
Serve chilled with various kinds of crackers or chips.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Rub butter around the inside of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Crumble raw beef into dish, sprinkle rice and onion soup mix over meat.
Mix mushroom soup and water in small bowl, pour over the rice mixture.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with green salad or baked potato.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix flour and oatmeal (bit by bit) in blender until it is a fine powder.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chips and grated chocolate.
Roll into golf size balls and mash down a little. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate peanut squares(microwave)
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine and 2 ounces chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred every 30 seconds. Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan; chill 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended, spread over crust.
Chill 30 minutes. Microwave remaining margarine and chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes 48 bars.
Prep time:
30 minutes plus chilling.

title: real french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
While yeast softens, sift flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir in dissolved yeast. Add enough of second cup of water to hold dough together.
Mix well until you have a sticky dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and knead.
Give it a good beating.
Divide into equal parts.
Place in a greased baking dish or loaf pan.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 400°.
For a harder crust, brush top with egg whites.

title: rocky mountain apple crisp
directions: Grease a 2-quart round baking dish. Arrange apples in bottom. Sprinkle with cinnamon, lemon peel, orange peel and liqueur.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, salt and butter.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle this over the apples and spices.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Place 1/2 of cream cheese, split lengthwise on serving dish. Layer onion, sauce and crab meat on cream cheese.
Cover with other half of cream cheese spread and with remaining sauce all over.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/3 cup fluid; flake. Combine salmon with bread crumbs, onion and parsley.

Add reserved salmon liquid, eggs, lemon juice and pepper; mix well. Shape into patties. Fry salmon patties in oil over medium heat until lightly browned on both sides. Serve hot. Garnish with lemon wedges. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread(2 loaves)
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add pumpkin and water.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon-cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crust off slices of bread; spread on cream cheese and roll up.
Slice in 1/2.
Dip each roll up in butter, then in the combined cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and pecans and/or coconut in mixing bowl; set aside.
Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil for 1 minute.
After removing from cooktop, add vanilla and pour over oatmeal mixture; mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and cool.

title: divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to a hard boil stage (260°) or until a small amount of mixture forms a hard boil when tested in very cold water.

Just before syrup reaches 260°, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Pour 2/3 of the syrup slowly over whites, beating constantly. Return the other 1/3 syrup back to the medium heat for 2 to 3 more minutes.
Pour remaining syrup over whites and beat until whites hold shape.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts or cherries before pouring into a lightly buttered dish or drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: cinnamon grits
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Slowly stir in grits.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until done.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cinnamon sugar to taste; stir until mixed.
Serve in bowls; top with cinnamon sugar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Amount of Wish-Bone dressing can be reduced.
Serve chilled.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: In large bowl mix ice cream, pudding, and candy.
Mix graham crackers and butter to make crust.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour ice cream mixture on top of graham crackers; top with cool-whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello and sugar together.
Dissolve in hot liquid or put on stove and bring to a boil.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add sliced strawberries.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve, then top with whipped cream before serving.

title: cranberry pake(pie-cake)
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with your favorite pie crust.
Into this put cranberries, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix margarine, 1 cup sugar, beaten eggs and flour.
Pour this batter over cranberries and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Great for the holidays!

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Chicken casserole preparation: Place peas and carrots in a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Cover with waxed paper; microwave on 100% (high) 10 minutes. Set vegetables aside. Coat chicken pieces with browning mix below; place coated pieces in a 2 1/2 quart casserole. Cover; microwave on 100% (high) for 20 to 25 minutes, rearranging chicken after 12 minutes. Pour drippings into a measuring cup; set aside. Remove chicken. Combine oil, onion, bell pepper and garlic in same casserole. Cover; Microwave on 100% (high) 3 minutes. Add water to drippings to make 2 cups. Add drippings, rice, salt, tomatoes and azafran to onion mixture. Cover; microwave on 70% (medium high) 7 minutes. Add chicken, peas and carrots. Cover and microwave on 70% (medium high) 5 minutes. Serve hot. Servings: 6.

title: donuts
directions: Combine water and yeast.
Let set 15 minues.
Add remaining ingrediens.
For extra softness, you may add a pack of instant mashed potatoes (prepared as on box) before adding all the flour. Dough will be a little sticky and does not need much kneading.
Use plenty flour to roll out.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to box, then cut both in half to make 4 layers.
Blend sugar; add sour cream.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend until creamy, then ice cake with mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut; keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter evenly.
Sprinkle evenly
the coconut, then chocolate chunks, then butterscotch morsels. Sprinkle nuts over top and press lightly.
After cooled, cut into bars.

title: carolina peach pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss the peaches with flour, nutmeg and salt. Turn the mixture into pie shell.
Pour cream over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: steamed broccoli
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Pour off all but 3 teaspoons drippings.
Saute onions in drippings.
Steam broccoli; drain. Put into dish.
Pour onions, bacon and walnuts over top and serve.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix the apricots or dates, coconut and sweetened condensed milk very well with spoon.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Keeps quite well.
Store, covered, in a cool location.
Better if refrigerated.

title: beef potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in greased baking dish the potatoes and onion. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover potatoes with water.
Mix hamburger, milk, oats, ketchup, onion, salt and pepper in bowl. Spread mixture evenly over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti and beef casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti, beef and sauce together.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pyrex dish. Top with cheddar and mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: breakfast sweet sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a jelly roll pan.
Place twisted strips on pan.
Spread pie filling over bread sticks.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While hot, drizzle with frosting. Cut into thirds.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Peel 2 or 3 medium-size potatoes; slice.
Arrange in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Brown and salt 1 pound ground beef.
Put on top of potatoes.
Mix together vegetable soup and mushroom soup; pour mixture over ground beef and potatoes.
Crush potato chips and put on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until browned.

title: old-time buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter or oleo soft.
Add sugar; cream together well. Add flour and beaten eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until tested done.
Cool completely before serving.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups semi-sweet morsels and nuts if desired.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup morsels.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Set aside. Saute minced onion in oleo. Blend in flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in milk and chicken broth.
Stir until thickened.
Mix white sauce and cooked chicken into the rice. Turn into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker or corn flake crumbs over top of crisp topping before baking.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hot bacon cheese spread
directions: Cut lengthwise slice from top of bread loaf; remove center, leaving 1-inch thick shell.
Cut removed bread into bite-size pieces; set aside.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Dissolve plain gelatin in cold water.
Mix them together.
Add grapefruit juice, ginger ale and sugar; mix all.
When it starts to set, add grapefruit sections.
Pour into oblong dish or mold and refrigerate.

title: bread loaf(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cook ground beef, sausage and onion, then drain. Hull out bread loaves. Mix meat, egg and the hulled out bread. Then layer cheese and meat mixture to fill hulled out loaves. Put the top of the bread back over loaf. Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 to 4-quart saucepan over low heat; let cool. Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture; mix well and chill. Form into 1 inch balls; roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart. Flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sherried beef
directions: Put beef in casserole.
Add mushroom soup and mushrooms. Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Add dry sherry.
Cover casserole dish.
Bake approximately 3 hours in a 325° oven.
Do not open. The last 1/2 hour, bake uncovered.
(Check for doneness.)
Use large casserole dish, or it may boil over.

title: chocolate tarts
directions: Blend together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook until mixture comes to a hard boil, stirring constantly.
When thickened, add vanilla and pour into baked tart shells.
Top with meringue and brown lightly in 475° oven.
Yields 8 tarts.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl and then combine with milk and cooking oil.
Stir until just moistened. Drop by tablespoons into bubbling stew or boiling chicken parts with broth for dumplings.
Cover tightly; let mixture return to boiling.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes without removing cover.
Double recipe for larger amount.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Add soda and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar and salad oil.
Then add bananas and eggs, one at a time; beat.
Sift flour.
Add in gradually nuts and raisins with flour.
Stir all together.
Bake at 350° until done.
Wait 36 hours before cutting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first
3 ingredients well and add eggs.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Pour	in
unbaked pie crust.	Place in preheated oven.
Bake
at
for	15 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and continue to bake for 25 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; add brown
sugar.
Let
cool.
Add egg and rest of ingredients.
Add
cup
chopped nuts, if desired. Spread in well-greased 8
x
8-inch
baking pan. Then sprinkle 1/2 cup chocolate chips over
the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle or large skillet over medium-low heat while you make the batter.
Beat together the milk and egg yolks.
Mix the dry ingredients.
Beat the egg whites with a whisk or electric mixer until stiff but not dry.
Combine the dry ingredients and milk-yolk mixture, stirring to blend.

Gently fold in the beaten egg whites; they should remain somewhat distinct in the batter. Add about 1 teaspoon of butter or oil to the griddle or skillet and, when it is hot, add the batter by the heaping tablespoon, making sure to include some of the egg whites in each spoonful. Cook until lightly browned on the bottom, 3 to 5 minutes, then turn and cook until the second side is brown.
Serve, or hold in a 200 degree oven for up to 15 minutes.

title: beer cheese
directions: Soften at room temperature the Cheddar and the cream cheese. Mix half Cheddar with half cream cheese, then add rest of cheeses and other ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve with small bread sticks.
Keeps in the refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: peach-praline cobbler
directions: In a Dutch oven combine peaches, 1 cup sugar, water, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Transfer to a 3-quart rectangular baking dish.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a Dutch oven over medium high heat.
Add onions, carrots, celery and garlic.
Cook 10 to12 minutes until vegetables are softened.
Add chicken broth, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce and pepper;
bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken al forno
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large, shallow baking dish, place chicken; pour dressing over.
Bake 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Turn chicken.
Add vegetables (except tomatoes) and cheese.
Bake until chicken is tender.
Add tomatoes and bake 5 minutes more.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar with a whisk (or by mixer) until sugar is dissolved; add water, milk, salt and vanilla.
Place in dish, then bake 30 to 45 minutes at 300° in pan containing 1-inch water.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese by directions on the box.
When completed, add 1 egg.
Mix well.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next, spread a jar of Ragu pizza sauce.
Add toppings of your choice and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan.
Add salt and grits.
Cook until done, following directions on package.
Remove from heat. Stir a couple of tablespoons of grits into beaten eggs.
Add back to the grits.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix together cream soup, drained Veg-All, Pet milk and onion.
Put 1/2 Pepperidge Farm mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 cream mixture. Put all of cut up chicken.
Pour other half of cream mixture. Top with rest of Pepperidge Farm mix.
Pour 1 1/2 cups chicken broth over pie.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Sift together baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour and milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potato wedges
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
In plastic bag mix flour, Parmesan cheese and a dash each of salt and pepper.
Add several potato wedges and shake until wedges are covered. Place wedges in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed butter mixture.
Add flavoring; mix.
Preheat oven to 350°; cook for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Lay out on paper towel for 20 minutes.
Dip each slice in flour. Brown eggplant quickly over medium heat.
Pour 1/4 of tomato sauce in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 eggplant slices, 1/3 tomato sauce and 1/3 of cheese.
Cover and bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: courtney's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until juices run clear. Drain and cool.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In a medium salad bowl combine peas, onion, green pepper, and garlic.
Stir together all remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Chill.
Cover for at least 12 hours in refrigerator.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: *If desired, substitute 1 (16 ounce) bag any frozen vegetable combination, cooked and drained, for fresh vegetables.

title: grated "drunk" sweet potatoes
directions: Mix
all ingredients (except potatoes) well.
Pour this mixture over potatoes and stir well.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: celery salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar well.
Add cinnamon, allspice, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to liquid mixture.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs together with an eggbeater.
Add flour, salt and rhubarb.
Bake until thick at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 2 (9 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saut onion, celery and pepper in drippings. Do not allow to brown. Add flour and stir until moistened. Slowly add tomatoes and ketchup, stirring to blend. Add Worcestershire sauce and salt, mixing well. Add cooked shrimp long enough to get hot, just before serving. Serve over mounds of cooked rice. Can be frozen.

title: soft cheese dip
directions: Cream the margarine until light and fluffy.
Add cheese, parsley, jalapeno chili and sauces until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked jumbo shrimp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Peel shrimp.
Make a shallow cut lengthwise down back of each shrimp; wash out vein.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place shrimp in oil.
Sprinkle with parsley, onions and garlic.
Drizzle with wine and lemon juice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink.

title: artichoke bottoms with mushrooms
directions: Cook artichoke bottoms according to package directions.
Drain well. Place in a buttered baking dish.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: oriental salad
directions: Pour 1 jar Zesty Italian dressing over vegetables.
Let sit for at least 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix noodles, broccoli, chicken and mushrooms.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Mix together soups and pour over top.
Top dish with fat-free cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: *shrimp and macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni according to instructions on box.
Make white sauce by melting shortening and adding flour and salt, then stirring in milk slowly.
Put into casserole a layer of macaroni, a layer of shrimp, a layer of pieces of cheese and pour on the white sauce.
Continue to do this until bowl is filled.
Cover top with bread crumbs and dot crumbs with butter for better flavor. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Simmer butter, cream cheese, garlic, Velveeta cheese and milk in a nonstick saucepan, stirring frequently.
When mixture is hot, add Parmesan cheese and shrimp or lobster.
Serve over cooked fettuccine and top with fresh parsley.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Brown garlic in 2 tablespoons of butter and add to 2-quart saucepan.
Drain liquid from clams into saucepan.
While simmering, add white wine.
Thicken with flour mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste and add the clams.
Keep on low heat. Meanwhile, boil linguine in salt water with small amount of oil to prevent sticking.
Drain and add sauce to linguine.
Top with fresh grated cheese and ground pepper.

title: almondigas with tomato sauce
directions: Mix the pork, flour and eggs in a bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Form into small balls.
This amount will yield around 20 to 24 balls.
Fry in hot oil.
Set aside.
In another pan, saute the garlic in 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Add the onions, the tomato sauce and stock.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the fried meat balls.
Cover and cook for another 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt margarine, then mix graham crackers together with margarine.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Cream together powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese; spread evenly over graham cracker mixture, then pour cherry pie filling over cream mixture evenly.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Peel, cut in half, and slice onion so slices are still fairly large.
Saute in butter until it starts to become translucent, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with flour, stir and cook continuously so flour can begin to cook.
Add cans of broth and parsley.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Put in bowls, add croutons and sprinkled cheese if desired.

title: nestle toll house pan cookie
directions: Prepare dough.
Spread into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice thin and cook carrots and salt in water until tender; drain.
Mix other ingredients with carrots; let stand overnight.
Good hot or cold.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from water.
Cool and cut into pieces.
Crumble breads.
Add all ingredients, except the margarine.
Stir well.
Pour into crock-pot.
Dot with margarine. Cover and cook on high for 2 hours or on low for 3 to 4 hours. When done, remove lid and fluff with fork.
Let cool 15 to 30 minutes before serving.
(Chicken should be boneless and skinless.)

title: cheddar dill knots
directions: Generously grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine roll mix with included yeast packet, cheese, and dill; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup hot water, butter, mustard, and egg until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Shape into a ball with greased or floured hands.
Knead for 5 minutes until smooth, sprinkling with more flour if needed. Cover dough with large bowl; let rise for 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 20 pieces.
On lightly floured surface, roll each piece into 8-inch rope; tie into a loose knot.
Place 2-3 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Cover loosely with greased plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place (80-85°) for 25 minutes or until almost double in size.
Heat oven to 375°.
Uncover dough.
In small bowl, beat all glaze ingredients; lightly brush over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 13-18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Make graham cracker crust in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°. Let cool.

title: chicken dressing
directions: If not using canned broth, boil a whole chicken.
Make a large skillet of corn bread; don't let it get real brown, just well done.
In large bowl, mix onion, celery, 2 slices of bread, shortening, seasoning and 2 cups of broth and let set until it is all moist.
Crumble corn bread in bowl.
Stirring constantly, add eggs fast so not to cook with corn bread.
Add a little bread at a time.
Taste for seasoning amount before baking.
Add salt and pepper.
Add margarine to pan before mixture.
Bake at 500° in preheated oven until brown peaks form on top.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Pour over 4 cups coarse bread crumbs (I use day old French bread torn into small chunks).
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in baking pan with about 1/2-inch water.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix and make marble size balls. Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork to flatten and make checked design. Bake at 350° until golden and crisp, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green chili cornbread
directions: Spray large cast-iron skillet with Pam.
Heat oven to 400°. Mix flour, corn meal, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Stir in milk, oil and egg whites until fairly smooth.
Fold in chilies and corn.
Spread in skillet.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown and pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Slice like pie and serve.

title: andouille and red grape stuffed roulade of beef
directions: Butterfly filet so it opens flat and lightly pound.
In a separate pan place butter, sausage and onion; saute until onions are golden brown.
Add 1 1/4 cups of the grapes with 1 pinch fresh thyme.
Deglaze pan with 1/8 cup of Port wine.
Take off fire and mix in bread crumbs to bind and let mixture cool.
Stuff filet with mixture and roll tightly.
Tie with butcher's string.
Season with salt and black pepper and sear in a lightly oiled hot pan giving color to all sides.
Remove filet to a roasting pan.
Place in a 350° oven and cook 25 to 30 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 125° to 130° for rare to medium rare. Remove from oven and let meat stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: luscious lime pie
directions: In top of
double
boiler soften gelatin in cold water. Add dash
of
salt
and egg yolks; cook and stir over hot (not boiling)
water
until mixture is slightly thick.
Remove from heat
and
stir in concentrate.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until
mixture
mounds slightly when spooned.
Beat egg whites until
soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold
in gelatin mixture, then whipped cream.
Add few drops
green
food	coloring.
Pile
into cooled pastry shell. Chill until
firm.	Top with whipped cream and lime slices and pomegranate seed (optional).
Makes 1 pie.

title: fruit and cereal brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix cereal and orange juice in large bowl.
Let stand about 2 minutes or until soft.
Mix in oil, egg and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Streusel Topping.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 45 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: peanut butter 'n banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With electric beater, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs, beating until well mixed.
Sift together dry ingredients 3 times. Blend with banana mixture but do not overmix.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until firm in the centers and the edges begin to separate from pans.
Cool on a rack for 10 minutes before removing from pans.
These freeze beautifully.

title: jiffy chicken
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed on box; set aside. Butter 9 x 13-inch pan and layer Stove Top stuffing, shredded chicken, sliced water chestnuts, mushrooms, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 chicken soup.
Do a second layer of chicken, water chestnuts, mushrooms, soup, then top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, whisk together shortening, cinnamon applesauce, sugars, egg and vanilla until shortening breaks into pea size pieces.
Add flour mixture to applesauce mixture. Mix well.
Fold in oats and then raisins. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes. Remove and place on cooling rack.
Makes 36 cookies.
Per serving contains 60 calories and 1.1 gram fat.

title: butter cream icing
directions: In
large
mixing
bowl,
cream butter or margarine and shortening	together.
Add	vanilla.
Gradually add 10x sugar, one cup
at a time, beating very well.
Beat on medium speed. Scrape sides and
bottom
of bowl often.
Add milk and beat at high speed until
light
and	fluffy.
Will
keep
very well, covered tightly, in refrigerator for several weeks.
Great for decorating fancy
cakes.
Set	out
at room temperature before using.

title: asparagus stir-fry
directions: Snap off base of asparagus and snap into 2-inch lengths.
In a small bowl, blend small amount of water and cornstarch.
Stir in soy sauce and set aside.
Stir-fry asparagus and green onions in oil for about 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and cook another minute.
Add your liquid and simmer.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: debbie's bacon and potato chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon, onion and celery until bacon is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Pour off drippings. Dice potatoes; add with broth, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Stir in soup, sour cream, milk and parsley.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans. Brown meat and stir in Chili-O mix, tomatoes, seasonings and onion. Add beans; cook down to desired consistency. Can serve with rice or tortilla chips. Top with cheese. Can eat as a dip.

title: bisquick pie crust(the best for strawberry pie)
directions: Mix ingredients together until ball is formed.
Spread and shape in 9-inch pan.
Prick all over with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and fill with fresh glazed strawberries.

title: three bean stew with vegetables
directions: Chop onions and tomatoes.
Peel and slice carrots 1/4-inch thick.
Seed and mince the jalapenos.
Heat oil in medium saucepan.
Add the onions and carrots.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer for about 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, jalapenos, corn, beans with their juices and chilies.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or 45 minutes for a more mellow flavor.
Good over pasta or rice.

title: cheese-egg fondue
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove crust from bread and put one layer of bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer your choice of filling and 1/2 of cheese.
Cover with the remaining slices of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together and pour over bread.
Bake uncovered 1 hour or until center is set.
Prior to baking completion, add remaining half of cheese to allow for melting. Serve immediately.
Can be prepared ahead of time and left in refrigerator.
Allow for extra baking time.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, warm water and sugar; let stand for 7 minutes for yeast to activate.
In a separate bowl mix eggs, salt and oil.
Add mixture to activated yeast mixture; mix well.
Start adding flour until sticky & starts pulling away from sides of bowl.
Let rise 1 hour or until double in size.
Place ball of dough on floured surface, pinch off and form into rolls, place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven until light golden brown.
Take out and spread butter on top of rolls.

title: chicken veggie casserole
directions: Place chicken in a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with the carrots, potatoes and celery.
Combine the soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 5 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; leave overnight.
Next morning, drain, then add other ingredients.
Refrigerate a few hours.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a bowl or Pyrex baking dish, drain artichoke juice only 1/2 way.
Add grated cheese and may.
Mix together with a fork.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: holiday bread rolls with fillings
directions: Put sugar in a bowl.
Add dissolved yeast, sour cream, eggs, butter and salt.
Slowly stir in flour. Break dough into 3 or 4 parts and roll out immediately. Brush dough with melted butter and then spread with your favorite filling:
nut, prune, poppy or cheese.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat together egg yolks, milk, Bisquick and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: osagood pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar and rest of ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into already baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites and some sugar and brown or put Cool Whip on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender.
Cut into small pieces. Drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together over slow heat until cheese melts.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Coat crumbs with margarine.
Cook about 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until the casserole begins to bubble.

title: jamaican cook up
directions: Parboil spinach, then chop.
Parboil shrimp.
If large, cut up. Cut tomato and onion small.
Add margarine.
Let sauce with shrimp and spinach for 15 minutes.
Add rice and water enough to cover. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until rice is tender on low fire.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In baking pan, sift dry ingredients.
Add softened butter and mix well together.
Add milk to dry ingredients.
Arrange peach slices over batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's sweet stewed tomatoes(pennsylvania dutch))
directions: Saute onion in Crisco oil.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add chopped tomatoes and brown sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: curried chicken casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Blend eggs with cream and corn.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Spoon into greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in preheated slow (325°) oven about 45 minutes.
Garnish with crisp bacon bits, if desired.

title: "dawn's caesar dressing"
directions: Beat eggs gently (not frothy).
Blend thoroughly with anchovy paste, garlic, chili powder and Romano cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and soup mix well, then blend all together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: orange glazed beets
directions: Heat beets in their own liquid.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat; add flour, brown sugar and orange juice.
Return to heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Drain beets; add sauce to beets.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Put pepper on a gas grill or broiler until pepper is blackened.
Take off grill and put in paper bag for 1/2 hour. Peel blackened skin off peppers.
Remove seeds.
Slice peppers ; add chopped garlic, oil, and salt and pepper
to taste.

title: fruit bell ringers
directions: Grind fruits and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape mixture into balls and roll in fine coconut, ground nuts or dip into softened chocolate.
Chill.

title: my favorite sauce
directions: Warm oil in large skillet.
Saute garlic, onion, basil, oregano, red peppers and pepper for about 3 minutes.
Add red wine, Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and crushed tomatoes.
Bring to almost boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Serve over linguini.

title: peanut butter oat brittle
directions: Combine oats, butter, salt and soda, not sugar.
Put sugar in a heavy skillet.
Place over moderate heat and stir constantly with a wooden spoon until sugar melts and becomes brown in color, caramelized.
When sugar has melted, remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter, oats, salt and soda.
Pour into a well-greased baking sheet.
Spread with spatula into thin pieces.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken, cheese and chips.
Layer chips.
Layer chicken.
Layer sauce.
Repeat and then top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cream cheese dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese; add powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add soups and rice and mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese and soup in a 4 ounce cup glass measure. Microwave at Medium 50% power 5 to 6 minutes or until soup and cheese are smooth.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add canned shrimp and next 3 ingredients.
Microwave at Medium 4 minutes.
Garnish with whole shrimp if desired.
Serve with sweet red or green pepper slices, endive and breadsticks.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with cold milk as directed on package. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the rocks into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers or gummy worms, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Mix jello and water.
Add berries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil together sugar, margarine and evaporated milk for 10 minutes, medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, graham cracker crumbs and nuts.

title: vermont corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add potatoes, milk and corn.
Heat to serving temperature.
Remove from heat and stir in Cheddar cheese until melted.
If necessary, return to low heat to finish melting cheese.

title: fresh tomato sauce (uncooked)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pasta) and heat until just warm. Serve over pasta.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add water, shortening, sugar, eggs and zucchini. Mix well. Add vanilla, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Stir well. Add nuts and raisins. Pour in well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix spaghetti, 1/2 can of broth and water.
Boil.
Drain and set aside.
Saute butter, 1/2 can broth, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in skillet.
Mix together Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, diced chicken and English peas.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: popovers
directions: Break egg in mixer bowl.
Beat until frothy.
Beat in milk and butter.
Slowly beat in flour and salt.
Batter should be light, but not foamy.
If batter becomes lumpy, strain it.
Bake in preheated 400° oven.
Oil custard cups or muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: corned beef pate
directions: Mix above with beater.
Press into mold or dish.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Ice with 1 ounce cream cheese and small amount milk.
Garnish with parsley or paprika.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: punch cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Dump crushed pineapple and blueberries.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 regular-size cake pans.
Spread Cool Whip over the cakes and refrigerate.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Pour pudding evenly into pie crust. Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Spoon Cool Whip to form top layer. Sprinkle crumbs of Oreo cookies over Cool Whip.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Mix cheese, milk, eggs, mayonnaise, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add hamburger and onion. Mix and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: opal's sweet pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, lime and water.
Set for 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, cloves, spice and salt. Cook until done.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In skillet brown ground beef.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasonings, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
In separate bowl, prepare corn bread mix according to box directions, except add 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon corn bread mixture around outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix pecans and coconut and spread into bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as per box directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Combine cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar and spread (or lob) over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dip for sliced apples
directions: Cream 1 package of regular or light (not whipped) cream cheese.
Add a little bit of mayonnaise, just to make the cream cheese spreadable.
Add 1 small can of crushed pineapple that has been well drained.
Add chopped dates and chopped pecans, until they look in equal portions to the cheese mixture.
Slice red and green apples, leaving the skins on.
Dip each slice in a mixture of citrus acid mixed with water or with fresh lemon juice, mixed with water.
Lightly wipe off slices with paper towels.
This prevents browning of the apple slices.
Place the spreadable dip in a bowl and in the middle of a large plate.
Arrange the slices in an attractive pattern around the dip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 4 slices bread on bottom of pan, then chicken and remaining mixture.
Then add cheese and rest of bread, crumbled on top. Bake 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix
and
pour into unbaked pie shell.	Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Pecans can be added, if desired.

title: microwave lemon piccata sauce
directions: To 2 cup
glass
measuring
cup
add
onion, butter and broth. Microwave on
High
minutes.
Whisk
in flour until smooth. Whisk in
lemon
juice,
then capers, then cream until desired thickness.	Serve over cooked fish, poultry or vegetables.	I always serve cooked rice on the side.

title: claudette's carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and beat well.
Add carrots, pineapple, coconut, walnuts and raisins; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 14-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup
and
milk
together.
Add beans and about 2/3 can of onions.
Sprinkle the remaining onions on top the last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine altogether, mixing well.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini about 5 minutes in salted water.
Take middles out of zucchini and dice.
Combine all of the ingredients and stuff into zucchini shells.
Dot stuffed shells with butter and place in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lemon-yogurt chicken
directions: In blender (or food processor) combine all ingredients except chicken.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in a large baking dish.
Pound cutlets to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place in baking dish.
Coat on both sides and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas goose
directions: Saute onion in oleo; soak bread in water and drain moisture. Add onion, bread, spices and sausage.
Stuff goose.
Place on roasting pan with 3 inches of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Drain water and baste for 2 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a square casserole and cover with aluminum foil.
Make slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit fizz punch
directions: In a large pitcher, pour water over tea bags.
Let stand 5 minutes, then remove tea bags.
In punch bowl, combine tea, juices and lemonade.
Before serving, add ginger ale and ice.

title: beefy cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese sit out to get it soft.
Take dried beef and cut into tiny little squares.
Add all ingredients together except nuts.
Mix well together and form a ball.
Roll ball in tiny little pieces of pecans to make your "cheese ball" type dip. Great with Wheat Thins, Sociables, etc.

title: bacon-stuffed flounder rolls
directions: Grease eight 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Set aside. Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings. Crumble and set aside. Measure drippings.
Add enough melted butter or margarine to equal 1/4 cup.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 pretty flower pot and 1 bunch pretty flowers.

title: cranberry salad dessert
directions: Grind cranberries and whole orange (not seeds).
Pour sugar over mixture and set overnight.
Mix Jell-O with hot water and jell until thick.
Add pineapple and juice with nuts to cranberry mixture, then add to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well and return to refrigerator to jell.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the rice in 1 1/2 cups of water until done; set aside.
Wash the zucchini thoroughly, trim ends and slice in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop the zucchini pulp and reserve for later use. Saute onion and garlic in oil until softened.
Add the chopped zucchini, red or green pepper, mushrooms, herbs, spices and salt and cook until the zucchini is softened.
Remove from heat; add the tomatoes and rice and mix well.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly with a fork.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Top with either chopped pecans or arrange halves.
Bake in a single pie crust.
The first 10 minutes, set the oven at 400°. Reduce the heat to 350° and bake until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine milk, biscuit mix and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.
Let cool for 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, cranberry juice and sugar. Chill. Stir in club soda. Pour over crushed ice.

title: apple bake
directions: Cut the apples into a 13 x 19-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs, flour, nutmeg to taste, baking powder and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Spread batter over the apples. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl with a fork; don't add milk all at once.
Dough should come away from the sides.
Put onto floured surface and cut into strips.
Dip strips in melted butter and then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, flour and salt.
Press in bottom and sides of flat baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 420° oven.
Cook and cool pudding.
Pour in crust.
Let stand until pudding is cold, then pour cherry pie filling over pudding and top with Dream Whip.

title: chicken and rice deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute the onion and green pepper in butter. Combine all ingredients except grated cheese and place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with cheese and cook 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted. Yield: 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown salt pork; saute onion in same pan until they are transparent.
Dice potato and boil until tender.
Add milk, corn, onion, pork and season to taste.
Heat through before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables for 10 minutes.
Drain and mix together with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.

title: rotini with peppers, pepperoni and mozzarella
directions: Cook the rotini in boiling, lightly salted water according to package directions.
In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat 1/2 cup of the chicken broth to boiling.
Add the garlic and simmer the mixture until it is fragrant, about 1 minute.
Add the pepperoni and cook 1 minute longer, stirring occasionally.
Add the three colors of peppers, remaining chicken broth, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 6 minutes or until the peppers are tender, but not mushy.
About half of the broth should have evaporated during the cooking.
Stir in the Mozzarella cheese and remove skillet from heat.
Drain the pasta thoroughly. Stir pasta into pepper mixture.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove 1/2 cup cookie dough and reserve. Add flour to remaining dough and knead to combine. Press dough into a 14-inch circle on 15-inch pizza pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool 10 minutes. Loosen from pan and cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie. Peel, core and slice apples.
Dip slices in soda to prevent browning.
Arrange apples on cream cheese.
Heat caramel topping slightly and drizzle over apples.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over pizza.
Cut into pieces and serve. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and reserve egg whites for meringue.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown and filling is set, about 30 minutes.

title: german soup
directions: Peel tomatoes and quarter into dishpan.
Cut off corn and add to tomatoes.
Add minced onions and all other ingredients.
Simmer for about thirty minutes.
Place in clean, sterilized quart jars. Can on 10 pounds pressure for fifteen minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats. Let stand 30 minutes. Cream butter or margarine and sugars. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all well. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, combine eggs and pumpkin.
Add sugar, salt and spices to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in milk and molasses; blend.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: wedding punch
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed on can.
Mix with Hawaiian Punch, pineapple juice, fruit cocktail and water in a large punch bowl.
Scoop sherbet into punch and serve.

title: hawaiian style stew
directions: In a large saucepot, heat oil.
Brown meat.
Stir in garlic, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Add water to cover.
Cover; bring to a boil, lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add green beans and cook for 5 more minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie shell. Spread half of the cherry pie filling in bottom. Set rest of filling aside.
Bake shell 15 minutes or just until crust is golden. Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread sticks.
Mix well.
Place dough on a cookie sheet according to package directions.
Spread lightly with margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with remaining mixture.
Makes 8 bread sticks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, chicken broth, pepper, salt and milk.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
After mixture is thick, add chicken, peas and corn; heat thoroughly. Spoon mixture into 8-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Keep warm.
Unroll crescent rolls into 2 rectangles.
Place rectangles over chicken mixture to form complete crust.
Press perforations together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until crust is browned.

title: easy bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine refried beans, jalapeno relish and enchilada sauce together in a bowl, mixing together.
Add 6 ounces of cheese and mix (add fresh jalapenos, optional).
Wipe inside of bowl with paper towel (this keeps from burning the inside of the bowl.)
Sprinkle with remaining 2 ounces of cheese.
Cover and place in oven for about 15 minutes.
Stir and cook for 15 minutes longer or until bubbling or cover and microwave for about 10 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Dip tortilla chips.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir the beef and onion in butter until tender; stir in garlic salt, flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: orange glazed roast chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Salt cavities lightly.
Melt butter; set aside 1 tablespoon for brushing chicken.
Stir onion into rest of melted butter; saute until soft.
Stir in water and 1/2 cup of the orange juice concentrate; heat to boiling.
Pour over stuffing mix in a bowl; toss until evenly moist.
Stuff into neck and body cavities of chicken.
Skewer neck skin to back; twist wing tips flat against back.
Fasten body cavities openings with skewers and string; tie legs to tail.
Place chicken, breast side up, on a rack in a small roasting pan.
Brush melted butter over chicken.
Roast 2 1/4 hours at 350° in a preheated oven.

title: crazy dip
directions: Mix all together.
Last add Krazy salt to taste.
Good with chips and vegetables.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Simmer beans, water and meat in covered kettle 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add water if needed.
Fry onion, celery, garlic and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add to soup with tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer at least 30 minutes longer.

title: ready-when-you-are biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, sugar and salt and set aside.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and soda, then cut in shortening until it resembles small peas.
Add liquid ingredients and mix lightly, but do not knead the dough.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 3 days.

title: green salad
directions: Line bottom of bowl with lettuce.
Add next 6 ingredients in layers.
Top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle on heavy layer of Parmesan cheese.
Let chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: my favorite pork chop dinner
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chops in mixture.
Preheat electric skillet to 360°; add oleo.
Brown chops on both sides.
Add 1/2 cup of water, cover and open vent. Set dish at medium.
Simmer and time dish for 30 minutes.
After frypan shuts off, lay corn and broccoli in frypan and add remaining 3/4 cup water.
Close vent and continue simmering for 10 to 13 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spread over top of first.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: glazed sweet potatoes(microwave)
directions: Pierce potatoes and place in oven.
Microwave for 8 or 9 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Peel and slice into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, then sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter. Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave for 4 minutes. Stir and microwave for 3 or 4 minutes, or until hot.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in small casserole dish and bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian french dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a jar.
Before putting garlic pod in, slightly bruise.
Place in refrigerator.
After 2 or 3 days, remove garlic.
Use on salads as any other sauce or dressing.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix both packages of pudding with milk, using an electric mixer.
Mix in the Cool Whip.
Line the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers (do not crumb crackers). Use whole crackers and do not overlap.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Pour balance of pudding mixture over crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and then frost with Eclair Icing.

title: mary's bread pudding
directions: Mix bread and milk together and let soak three minutes.
Add salt, butter and sugar.
Pour mixture over eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for about 50 minutes, until firm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool mixture.
Add other ingredients and a little salt and pepper, if desired.
Let mixture cool completely before serving.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and oats in a separate bowl.
Cream together the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour flour mixture into the creamed mixture and mix thoroughly. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Cook just until golden brown.
Remove and let cool.

title: wild duck with orange sauce
directions: Chop celery, onions, apples and oranges.
Clean, wash and dry ducks thoroughly.
Pack tightly in roasting pan and cover with water.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Discard fatty cooking water. Clean, wash and dry ducks again.
Stuff each with celery, onions, apples and oranges.
Pack them tightly into clean pan (breast down).
Add spices and cover with juice, stock and wine.
Cover and bake 4 to 5 hours (depending on size of ducks).
Use several cups to fill saucepan.
Reduce until thickened (you may also use cornstarch).
Add Grand Marnier to taste.

title: baked apple and carrot casserole
directions: Place layer of apples, then layer of carrots, then sprinkle with mixture of sugar and flour.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour juice over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan cream cheese cake
directions: Butter a 2-quart Bundt pan heavily, using 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with the 1/3 cup finely chopped nuts, then the 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Cream 1 cup butter with cream cheese and remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, until thoroughly blended.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in remaining pecans.
Beat egg whites stiff, then fold into creamed mixture. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven one hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in cake pan on rack for 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack to cool.

title: anna mae's chocolate and biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk, water and butter. Simmer over low heat until thick.
(I usually make biscuits while it is simmering.)
Serve over hot buttered biscuits or toast.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat milk in microwave for 4 minutes (until real bubbly), stirring twice.
Add chocolate chips to milk; stir until melted. Add pecans.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Day 1:
Line a long pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place the meat in the foil and pour 1/3 c. liquid smoke over the meat. Sprinkle with the salts.
Seal foil tightly to refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate candy drops
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the chocolate almond bark. Shape into balls and refrigerate.
The balls should be smooth, not sticky.
If they are too sticky to handle, you may want to add more powdered sugar.
Place the candy balls on cookie sheets covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dip into melted chocolate.
You melt chocolate in double boiler or in microwave. These candies are good without the chocolate, also.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press rounded measuring tablespoonful of crumb mixture onto bottom of each of six paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.

title: elaine allen's fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients together, but do not stir until left overnight.
For larger amount, double recipe.

title: congealed applesauce salad
directions: Slowly bring applesauce to a boil. Add jello and dissolve. Add crushed pineapple, Coke and lemon juice (one at a time), stirring after each addition. Congeal.
Serves 12.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place 3 cups lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs on top of the lettuce in the bowl.
Sprinkle with more salt, if desired.
Layer in order: peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and Swiss cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Garnish with green onions and paprika.
Salad can be tossed before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: calico beans and beef
directions: Brown the bacon and onions.
Add the beef and cook mixture well. Add the beans and remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Bake uncovered in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix oatmeal, eggs, pecans, onion, milk and seasoning in bowl. Make into patties and fry in skillet.
Put cooked patties in baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup over and heat in oven.

title: butterscotch bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bread crumbs in buttered 2 1/2 cup casserole dish.
Beat egg slightly.
Stir in butter, milk, brown sugar, seasonings and raisins.
Pour egg mixture on bread crumbs. Bake until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
top with light cream, if you like.
Serves only two.

title: ham and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Slowly stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened. Add cheese, ham and green pepper to sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash yams.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla, coconut and 1/2 stick margarine.
Mix well.
Put in large casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, pecans (chopped), 1/2 cup flour and stick melted margarine.
Mix well.
Spread on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

directions: Add the

Cool and set aside.

title: chili beans
directions: Melt shortening in pan.
Add chopped onion and beef; cook and stir until brown.
Add seasoning, tomato soup and kidney beans. Cook slowly, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
