Crumble cake into mixture and fold gently until cake is coated.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice strawberries and lay on top until completely covered with berries.
Cover with strawberry glaze.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Microwave until thickened, 10 to 12 minutes on High, stirring every 4 minutes.
Pam spray 9-inch pie plate.
Slice strawberries. Put 2 cups into pie plate.
Pour syrup over berries.
Chill at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Stuff peppers.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° or until desired tenderness of peppers.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: beaver-wild meat
directions: Clean beaver and be sure curnels under legs are out; take off all fat.
Cut in pieces; wash good.
Put in a pan a layer of beaver, a layer of onions and sprinkle heavy with salt.
Continue this way until pan is full.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse thoroughly.
Put a layer of meat and brush with plum jelly. Continue until roaster is full.
Bake at 350° for 4 to 5 hours or until done.

title: french fries
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2 inch wide sticks. Place in bowl of ice water about 30 minutes to crisp, then drain.

Pat dry with paper towels. Place sticks into plastic bag and add oil, paprika and salt. Shake to coat. Place on large cookie sheet in single layer. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Stir once or twice. Bake at 450° for last 10 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: You will need jars and seals.

title: rice pudding
directions: To Soften Raisins:
Pour a little water over raisins.
Heat, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: parsley in sesame sauce(tahini)
directions: Combine tahini, lemon juice, salt and garlic; mix thoroughly. If mixture is too thick, add a little water.
Combine with parsley and mix well.
Serve with fish or as a side dish with fried vegetables.
Serve as an appetizer with wedges of Arabic bread.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and water. Cook at 230°. Add peanuts. Cook at 290°. Add baking soda and salt. Mix until it starts to foam. Pour out on a lightly oiled cookie sheet. Loosen as it cools and stretch it. Turn it over.

title: chicken breast spruce cove style
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chicken and soup.
Fill each chicken breast with mixture.
Secure.
Place, seam side down, in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish (rectangular).
Place any extra filling between chicken breasts.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: 10 minute toffee
directions: In frying pan, combine all ingredients except nuts and chocolate.
Turn heat to high and stir constantly in 1 direction until mixture begins to thicken and darken (about 10 minutes). Quickly stir in almonds.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet. Spread evenly with spatula or wooden spoon.

Break chocolate into pieces on top of mixture. As chocolate melts, spread evenly over toffee mixture. Freeze 1 to 2 hours until hard. Break into pieces while still frozen. Can be stored at room temperature.

title: oat bars
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan prepared with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: madge's egg pie
directions: Mix well.
Put into deep dish pie crust.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma clippard's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg, almond flavoring and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Measure and sift flour, stir dry ingredients together and blend.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough in half and roll.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: joycelyn's ice cream sandwich
directions: Layer 12 frozen ice cream sandwiches on bottom of container. Spread 1 Cool Whip over ice cream sandwiches. Squeeze 1/2 caramel sauce over Cool Whip. Squeeze 1/2 magic chocolate sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts. Layer remaining 12 frozen ice cream sandwiches. Spread 1 Cool Whip over ice cream sandwiches. Squeeze 1/2 caramel sauce over Cool Whip. Squeeze 1/2 magic chocolate sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts. Garnish with cherries. Keep frozen until ready to serve. (Freeze overnight.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Blend in molasses and buttermilk.
Combine flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon and add to previous mixture.
Beat until smooth or use electric mixer. Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares. Serve warm with whipped topping, applesauce or warm lemon sauce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles and drain.
Rinse with cold water. Cut up cucumber, broccoli, tomato, ham, cheese into small pieces. Open the mushrooms and olives.
Add all ingredients to the spaghetti.
Finally add the Italian dressing and toss. Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: soup
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Turn on low.
Cook 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir in pecans.
Mix well. Spread pecans evenly in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In hot oil, saute onion, pepper and garlic.
Add wine, pepper, salt and Italian seasoning.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes more or until shrimp are pink.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave.
Stir melted Hershey bars and half of Cool Whip together.
Pour in pie shell.
Cover with regular Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: ruby r. lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Then mix eggs, oil, cake mix and cooled Jell-O.
Bake for the time stated on cake mix box. Do not use chiffon cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Cook noodles, onion and celery in chicken broth. Skin and debone chicken.
Add noodles, 3/4 of cheese, soup and pepper.
Put in large casserole.
Put in enough broth so it won't be dry.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Put rest of cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: molasses cookies(over 100 years old.  by my grandma, minerva wheeler.)
directions: Drop by teaspoon and bake in moderate oven (350°) until brown.

title: coconut-pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Drain pineapple and spread over top of cake.
Prepare
instant pudding according to directions.
Pour over layer of pineapple. Sprinkle part of coconut and nuts on top of pudding.
Spread on Cool Whip. Sprinkle with more coconut and nuts.

title: jumer hotel rest rolls
directions: Stir Bisquick and yeast together.
Roll dough out to 18 x 26-inch rectangle.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cut dough crosswise into 4ths.
Roll inch 4th from long side.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Snip each roll almost through at intervals.
Use scissors.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If not brown enough, bake 2 minutes under broiler.

title: ham and cheese snacks
directions: Place rolls in freezer for 20 minutes.
Combine butter, mustard, onion flakes, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together.
Mix until creamy; set aside.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Strain pineapple to drain out all juice.
Add lime jello, then all cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well in bowl.
Leave in that bowl or pour in a loaf pan.

title: yam cookies
directions: Cook yams; pour water off and add remaining ingredients.
Mash all together.
Spoon on cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: best baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces and fry until brown.
Drain fat off; add onion and cook just until tender.
Add catsup, mustard, brown sugar and beans; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: Cook all ingredients except rice in a pan for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cook at 375° in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or on stove top until heated through.

title: mexican haystack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer one hour.
To serve individually, put down Fritos first, then meat mixture, then shredded cheese, then cut up tomatoes and lettuce on top.
Serves 10.

title: venison stew
directions: Marinate meat in soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper for about 1 hour. Cover bottom of pot with oil and heat; add meat. Cook on low heat with lid on for about 30 minutes. Remove lid and cook until all water is gone and meat is real brown, stirring often. Remove meat from pot; cover with water. Cook, covered, 30 to 40 minutes; add gravy mix. Stir until all lumps are out. Cook on low about 30 minutes, covered.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs slowly, mixing well. Stir in nuts, then dry ingredients (sifted together twice).
Shape into long roll 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Put in refrigerator in greased pan overnight.
When ready to bake, slice thin and bake at 350° until brown.

title: ida's good pie
directions: Beat yolks slightly; add sugar, then spices, vinegar and butter.
Beat egg whites stiff and add to mixture.
Add nuts and raisins; bake in pie plate lined with pastry.
Do not bake crust first.
Serve with whipped cream.
This was my Great Grandmother's and did not come with an oven temperature or time to cook.
I use medium oven 350° and keep an eye on the pie.

title: ground beef hash
directions: Boil potatoes.
Brown meat and onion.
Add soups and water. Drain potatoes; add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Enjoy.

title: cookie raisin clusters(no-bake cookie)
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine, sugar, raisins, egg and milk. Bring to
a boil 2 minutes.
Add cereal, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool slightly.
Spoon by tablespoons onto coconut and roll to coat.
Chill.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: favorite super moist orange cake
directions: Mix the 4 ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and butter.
Add buttermilk, flavoring, salt, lemon juice and slightly beaten egg yolk.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake in a hot 425° oven until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in a slow oven for 20 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch shell and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs well; add sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla. Beat until well combined.
Stir in butter and pecans, mixing well. Turn into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes or until filling is set in center when pie is shaken gently.

title: schnetke
directions: Mix as for pie dough, then add 1 cup cream.
Mix so that it will hold together in a soft dough.
The less you work it the flakier it will be after baking.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add to chicken and all other ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix celery, water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup and pimentos in a quart casserole dish. Toss bread crumbs with almonds and oleo. Sprinkle on top of celery mixture. Sprinkle remaining almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Sprinkle pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Add filling and bake in hot oven at
450° for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with soup, milk and 1/2 can crumbled onion rings.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or 10 minutes on Full power in microwave).
Garnish with remaining crumbled onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer in oven (or 2 minutes in microwave).
Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: festival pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven (start in cold oven). Combine all ingredients. Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300° until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together; add to milk mixture.
Cook in skillet until thick.
Add butter or margarine and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and bake. Top with meringue.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top of pie.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: rocky road(microwave)
directions: Place chocolate in 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle. Microwave at High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir until evenly melted. Fold in marshmallows and walnuts; coat evenly.
Turn into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: great grandma's rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix together ingredients, except the rhubarb.
Put raw rhubarb in bottom of deep dish casserole and sprinkle with sugar (about a cup).
Pour the mixture on top of the rhubarb and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or golden brown.
Can substitute other fruits such as blueberries, apples or strawberries.

title: pot pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in enough milk to make a soft dough.
Roll half until very thin. Repeat with other half of dough.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Drop into chicken or beef broth.
Cook until insides are not doughy.

title: raspberry sherbet
directions: This can be made with any type of fresh fruit; no frozen fruit.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Place large, heavy skillet in the oven with some grease or oil or shortening.
Mix all ingredients.
When grease in skillet is very hot, pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shells.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat well; pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions and cook in salted water until tender; cool. Carefully remove center of each onion, leaving at least 2 layers for a shell.
Coarsely chop onion centers.
Add hamburger, salt, bay leaf (crumbled) and chopped parsley.
Mix well and stuff in onion shells.
Pour tomato juice over and around onions; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cupcake
directions: You will need cupcake liners.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Stir in brown sugar.
Mix butter in with fork.
Add rolled oats.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 crumb mixture in greased 8-inch pan.
Pour on cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fried quail
directions: Put about an inch of oil in frying pan and heat to medium. Salt and pepper inside and out.
Shake in flour.
Put in frypan and cook until done.
Allow 2 whole birds per person.

title: cranberry wine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then break up cranberry sauce in Jell-O mixture. Add all remaining ingredients. Pour into a serving dish or mold and chill until very firm. Unmold onto a plate of greens or serve directly from bowl. This is especially good with turkey or chicken. For all festive occasions.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine undrained mixed vegetables, onion, celery, mayonnaise, cheese, and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Top with mixture of cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and lemon juice.
Run cold water over crabmeat and drain.
Mix with cream cheese and chill.
Top with cocktail sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: On a cutting board, peel oranges and cut into bite sizes, removing seeds.
Peel and core apples and cut in bite sizes.
Slice bananas.
Place all fruit in a large mixing bowl and coat with salad dressing.
Add pecans and mix.
If more sweetness is desired, can add 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 cup orange juice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini and parmesan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan. Shred zucchini and onion.
Combine all ingredients, except eggs and oil.
Beat together eggs and oil and stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour into pan and smooth top.
Bake until edges are brown and center sets, about 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into 48 squares.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: cookies heavenly crescents
directions: Blend all ingredients together; pinch off enough dough to make a walnut size ball.
Then shape into crescents by rolling
by hand.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° on cookie sheet.
Roll in extra confectioners while still hot.

title: guri guri ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and freeze.
Stir, then re-freeze until firm.
Can pour into individual cups.

title: deep-dish taco squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 18-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage and taco filling.
Mix on low to medium heat, stirring often.
In a separate bowl mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.

title: brownie mix
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until evenly distributed.
Store in large airtight container in cupboard.
Keeps 10 to 12 weeks.

title: tacoritos
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Mix taco seasoning into hamburger; simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Put hamburger mixture into tortilla shells and wrap them up. Place into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour gravy over wrapped up tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and the gravy is hot and bubbly.

title: sugar biscuit
directions: Mix butter and sugar into beaten egg.
Add flour and cream. Roll out, very thin, on a floured board.
Place on buttered "iron pan" in 475° oven.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Heat milk, water, honey, butter and salt in a pan until warm (110° to 115°).
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups bread flour, 2 cups whole wheat flour and yeast.
Add warm liquids; beat 3 minutes on medium speed of mixer.
Add rest of whole wheat flour and enough bread flour to make very stiff dough.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup into ground beef along with 3/4 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Mix well.
Pour half of remaining sauce on bottom of baking dish.

title: pierogies
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients and roll out flat.
Cut dough into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Fill with potato and cheese filling; fold in half.
Press firmly around edges.
Boil in water, then fry in butter and onion.

title: banana supershake
directions: In blender, combine bananas, lemon juice, water and milk. Blend well.
Add ice, blending until smooth.
Serve in frosted glasses.
You can refrigerate any leftovers as mixture stays thick and creamy in refrigerator.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mona's deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in saucepan for 15 minutes.
Plunge into cold water to cool.
Peel eggs and cut in half.
Put yolks in a bowl.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Spoon into egg halves.
Sprinkle with paprika or curry.
Chill.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and add boiling water; stir while mixing. Beat egg yolks.
Add 2 tablespoons egg yolks to mixture, then add all together.
Let cook until thick.
Add lemon juice and batter. Top with egg whites and cook at 350° until meringue is brown. Makes 1 large pie.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix all together, then mix 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 2 tablespoons of margarine and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: wilted spinach lettuce salad
directions: Cut bacon slices into eighths and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Wash lettuce and tear into bite-sized pieces.
Remove stems from spinach and combine with lettuce in salad bowl.
Add the onions.
Cover and refrigerate until just before serving.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and water to the reserved bacon drippings.
Set aside until ready to serve.
At serving time, bring dressing mixture to boiling.
Stir and pour over lettuce-spinach mixture.
Toss and top with bacon bits.
Sprinkle with croutons and/or other toppings.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Brown hamburger with the onion and green pepper; drain.
Add 1 package spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and 1 1/4 (8 ounce) cans water.
Simmer over low heat about 20 minutes, or until all liquid is cooked in.
Make sure this meat mixture is cool before spreading on the dough.

title: almond cream soup
directions: Melt butter; add onion and celery and cook over low heat until tender.
Add flour, seasonings and condiment sauce; blend.
Stir in milk and cook over low heat until smooth and thickened.
Add bouillon cubes and stir to dissolve.
Stir in blanched almonds. Turn into hot soup bowls and sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 6.

title: thin pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Put a little oil on a griddle and pour batter in small amounts.
Brown on both sides.

title: party chicken
directions: Cover baking dish with beef.
Arrange chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 3 hours or at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: tami's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to slow boil and cook for 2 hours.
Stir often.
Remove bay leaves and serve with cheese and crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bread pan.
Combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Spoon in pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool completely before slicing.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan lightly.
Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl.
Add bananas, milk, oil and egg whites.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Spread batter in pan.

title: cran-raspberry chutney cream spread
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, or until thickened, stirring often.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: triple fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart saucepan, cook chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Blend cake mix to hot pudding. Mix 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
(Also good with coconut pudding.)

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Saute ground chuck in a little water.
Add other ingredients and cook until thick.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: corn casserole dish
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add corn and green beans and mix well. Add tomato sauce; salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into prepared 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned on top. Cut into squares.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add flour, salt and soda.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts on top of cake batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons dehydrated onion with 2 tablespoons water; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted margarine or butter, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon over chicken in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until chicken is done, turning occasionally and spooning butter-lemon sauce over chicken.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add seasoning mix as directed.
Cut up lettuce, onion and tomatoes; add cheese.
Crunch up nacho chips and add to salad.
Add cooked seasoned hamburger and the Catalina dressing.
Can be served with sour cream and taco sauce, if desired.

title: simply delicious southern fried chicken livers
directions: Wash livers and drain. Sprinkle with salt.
Pour milk into small bowl.
Put flour into small paper bag.
Dip livers in buttermilk. Sprinkle with seasoning, then shake in flour, shaking off excess.
Pour oil to 1-inch depth.
Heat to 350°.
Fry livers, a few at a time, turning once to brown on both sides.

title: curry rice chicken
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into small pieces.
Cook rice in 2 3/4 cups chicken broth, seasoned with curry powder, for 20 minutes.
Add onion.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Add chicken, green beans, water chestnuts, celery soup and mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients together well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Arrange stalks in greased 11 x 17-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt together in a saucepan.
Heat sugar syrup to 234° on a candy thermometer or until a little syrup forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Remove saucepan from range and place in cold water.
Add butter and peanut butter.
Let mixture cool to lukewarm without gloss; quickly add nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: cheese strata
directions: Spread bread with margarine; cut into cubes (approximately 1/2 x 1/2-inch).
In 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan, layer half of bread cubes.
Follow with half of grated cheese.
Repeat with bread, then cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, mix well and pour over bread/cheese mixture.
(Be sure to distribute onions evenly.)
Chill 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twin toddler super supper
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking dish with humming "The Barney Song," realizing you are the only one watching it.
Set aside.
Begin to brown ground beef.
Begin to boil water in medium saucepan for rice.
Go investigate large crash in toy room. Retrieve Twin #1 from third shelf of shelving unit.
Instruct them to pick up the pile of books that were knocked off fourth shelf of shelving unit.
Return to kitchen.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Add all ingredients.
May sprinkle top with chopped parsley before serving.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve cold.
Makes enough for 8 to 10 people as a side dish.
Great for picnic dish to pass.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, milk, egg yolks and butter in medium saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Make meringue by beating egg whites with sugar until stiff peaks form; fold in vanilla.
Spread meringue on pie and brown in a 400° oven.

title: lee's birthday chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for butter and bread crumbs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix bread crumbs and butter, then cover other mixture with this.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, water and pudding mix.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream, then strawberries and bananas.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture into pan and mix well with margarine.
Put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lazy doughnuts
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Drop batter from tablespoon into greased muffin pans and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and dip in melted butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Makes 3 dozen doughnuts.

title: broccoli casserole no. 2
directions: Cook
and
drain
broccoli.
Combine
mushroom soup and salad dressing.
Arrange
in layers in baking dish, broccoli, soup mixture,
eggs
and pimento, nuts and bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: fruit balls
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows; mix in saucepan over low heat. Mix other ingredients, except coconut, in large bowl.
Pour melted ingredients over it; stir well.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: turtles
directions: Melt in a double boiler.
Add coarsely chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Drop onto buttered wax paper.
Dip in chocolate.
Necessary chocolate can be purchased at a craft or candy shop.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Saute chicken in skillet sprayed with cooking oil spray until golden brown; remove.
In same pan, saute mushrooms with garlic salt or 1 clove minced garlic.
Add wine or sherry.
Stir in soup and remaining ingredients.
Return chicken; simmer for about 15 minutes, or until done.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: waldorf-astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk with salt alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Lastly, add baking soda and vinegar.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Cool completely before frosting.

title: fruit punch
directions: Hawaiian Punch can be used instead of orange juice for a nice change.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: old timey pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add eggs, then add sifted flour and baking powder alternately with milk and flavorings mixed together. Bake at 325° in a tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken too
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; pull off bone.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups.
In large baking dish, layer crushed chips, soup mixture and chopped onion, chicken pieces and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In a bowl beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, then lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze until firm.

title: yellow jello cake
directions: Mix and bake yellow cake according to package directions, in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

Let cool in pan. Take a toothpick and poke holes in the cake. Mix the Jello according to package directions and when it is lukewarm, pour 3/4 of Jello mix over cake. Cool in refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread hash browns in bottom of baking dish.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Add the chicken soup, sour cream, salt and pepper to onion mixture. Spread this mixture over the hash browns.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Sprinkle corn flakes over the cheese and dribble 1/2 cup melted butter over the corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rainbow float
directions: Fill glass halfway to the top with fruit punch.
Add sherbet. Fill the rest of glass with 7-Up.
Drink right away.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and water slowly to the hard boil stage. Stir during the latter part of the cooking to prevent burning. Remove from the fire and add butter, soda and vanilla and stir enough to mix.
Pour into a greased pan and when cool enough to handle, pull it until it becomes light in color.
Stretch into a long rope and cut with scissors into small pieces.

title: uncooked homemade ice cream
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; add milk and vanilla.
Pour into freezer container.
Add homogenized milk to fill-line of freezer container.
Freeze with ice cream freezer.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add and mix in the flour, baking soda and salt.
After all ingredients are mixed together, stir in the chocolate bits and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Use as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine cake mix with applesauce, eggs, orange and lemon extracts, mixing well.
Toss cherries, pineapple, dates and pecans with flour to coat.
Stir fruit and nuts into cake mixture, mixing well.
Turn mixture into two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 hours or until cake tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Spray 12-inch nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium heat. Sprinkle both sides of chicken with oregano, salt, garlic powder, pepper and cayenne pepper. Cook in skillet 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, until juice is no longer pink when center of thickest pieces are cut. Remove chicken from skillet. Keep warm. Melt butter in skillet over medium heat. Cook bell peppers and onion about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until crisp and tender. Stir in mushrooms. Cook 3 to 5 minutes until vegetables are tender. Place chicken in skillet; spoon vegetables over chicken. Sprinkle cheese over vegetables. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand until cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits, water and salt 5 minutes or until thick and bubbling.
While hot, add Velveeta, margarine, seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce.
When cool, add the well beaten eggs.
Pour into two 8 x 8-inch or one 9 x 15-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May want to let it sit 5 to 10 minutes after baking.
Will firm up as it cools.
Good with pork or ham.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch pan completely with wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips with milk, vanilla and salt; stir.
Add pecans.
Stir in marshmallows.
Cool in refrigerator until well set.

title: vidalia onion complete casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large casserole pan, make alternating layers (2 each) of onions, potatoes and chicken.
Mix together soup and margarine and spread evenly over the top of the casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Bake cake and set aside. Put strawberry syrup in top of double boiler. Add gelatin and stir until it is dissolved. Add strawberries; stir. Then chill until thickened. Whip cream until stiff; add sugar. Fold cream into thickened strawberry mixture and then frost cake and chill several hours before serving.

title: wine baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate several hours (not necessary however).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken, uncovered for 1 hour basting frequently.

title: quick beet pickles
directions: Drain beets and save 1 cup of the liquid. To the 1 cup of liquid add the rest of the ingredients. Heat to boiling. Pour over beets. Cool. Then keep in refrigerator.

title: crookneck squash pickles
directions: Wash squash and cut into thin slices.
Peel onions, then slice very thin.
Add to squash.
Cover squash and onions with water and add salt.
Let stand 2 hours and drain.
Bring all ingredients to a boil and heat 5 minutes.
Pack into jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Screw Kerr cap on firmly tight.

title: eggnog royale
directions: Chill large punch bowl and stir in eggnog, coffee and bourbon. In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream just until soft peaks form.
Fold into eggnog mixture.
Place ice cream balls on top and sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Serve at once.
Makes 15 cups.
Scoop up about 10 large ice cream balls.
Place on jelly roll pan and freeze.
Refrigerate eggnog.

title: creamy cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cauliflower, radishes and green pepper. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour over cauliflower mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cover bottom of large Dutch oven with olive oil.
Add peppers, onions, beef and mushrooms.
Cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce, stir well.
Add tomato puree.
Fill puree can 1/2 full of water and add also.
Add tomato paste.
Important:
Mix thoroughly or will stick to bottom of pan.
Add onion salt, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Add sugar and oregano last.
Stir well.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours on low heat.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: snowman's pudding
directions: Combine sugar, 2 cups water, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes with leeks and cream(8 servings)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add leeks and stir.
Cover and cook until leeks are tender.
Uncover and cook until almost all liquid is absorbed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or	until
done.
(Cook in tube or Bundt pan.) Delicious for freezing.

title: turkey-rice meatballs
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions to make one cup cooked rice; set aside to cool.
Combine ground turkey, egg, parsley, sage, thyme, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Add cooked rice to meat mixture; mix well.
Shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Brown meatballs on all sides.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Remove from skillet.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil together 5 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and add oranges. Bake according to directions on pkg, using two 9 inch round cake pans. Brown 1 cup coconut in 1 tsp. margarine and set aside. Soften the 1/3 cup margarine and cream cheese and mix well with sugar, milk, and remaining coconut. After cake has cooled, frost and sprinkle top and sides of cake with browned coconut.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix butter, milk and bread.
Stir in salmon, egg yolks, lemon juice, onions, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into salmon mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large brown paper bag sprayed with Pam; set aside.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, butter, Karo syrup and salt.
Stir and microwave 2 minutes.
Stir and repeat.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn in bag.
Stir well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain vegetables. Mix all ingredients, except margarine and crackers.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top. Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead dough about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Make rolls and let rise until double.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: mock oriental dinner
directions: Cook pineapple, butter and 1/3 cup pineapple syrup 5 minutes. Combine cornstarch and remaining 1/3 cup syrup to make thin paste. Gradually stir into pineapple mix.
Add soy sauce, vinegar and non-caloric sweetener.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Add tuna and mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Heat well. Prepare Durand's quick rice.
Place in deep platter.
Top with pineapple mixture.
Serve at once.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half the mixture over the graham crackers.
Layer more crackers over pudding and then pour rest of pudding mixture over and cover with another layer of crackers. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat on stove. Spread on cake and refrigerate for another 24 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
(I prefer to cream sugar and oil; then add beaten eggs.
Next, add all dry ingredients that have been sifted together.)
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Test with a toothpick.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling.
Freezes real well.

title: peaches
directions: Melt butter in an electric skillet.
Wash peaches.
Do not peel.
Slice peaches thin into melted butter until you have your pan full.
Sprinkle sugar over peaches.
Cook on slow until they resemble stewed dried peaches.
Stir frequently while cooking.

title: macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Cook peas and drain. Mix macaroni, peas, cheese, gherkins, mayonnaise and onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with cocktail rye bread or crackers.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Mix well. Spread on Triscuits.
Place in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix corn, peas, celery, pepper and onion.
Add cheese, sour cream, soup and seasoning mix and pour in casserole dish that is lightly greased or sprayed with Pam.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty vinaigrette dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine oil, Lea & Perrin's original Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mustard and garlic.
Whisk until creamy and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Whisk again immediately before serving.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 dish with graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Pour over grahams.
Pour Cool Whip over this.
Put another layer of grahams over this.
Put container of icing in microwave for 20 to 30 seconds so it will spread easily.
Spread this over top of grahams.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Shred chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: bloody mary slushes
directions: The night before serving, make slush mixture.
In food processor or electric blender, combine onion, Worcestershire, half the vegetable juice and all the lemon juice; process until smooth. Pour into shallow nonaluminum baking pan.
Stir in remaining vegetable juice.
Cover and freeze.

title: almond popcorn
directions: Mix nuts and popcorn in a large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar (or fructose), butter, corn syrup, and baking soda.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil and stir until mixture is golden, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in extract.
Pour over nut and popcorn mixture, and toss to coat. Cool slightly; break apart while warm.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: indian longhouse method of smoking fish
directions: Trim the ribs so that they are of approximately uniform thickness.
This usually involves making a fillet by removing a strip of meat from one side.
Make a superficial cut through the tough membrane between each pair of ribs.
Place the meat in boiling water for 10 minutes.
If you want to experiment, add some onions and/or spices to the water, including garlic, salt and pepper.

title: apple dessert casserole
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole, mix apples and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, blend milk, butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon over sugared apples, then sprinkle with topping, 1/4 cup chopped nuts and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy fruit pie
directions: Make batter of the flour, milk and sugar; reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix batter and pour into melted margarine in pan.
Pour in warm fruit; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Cut peaches into unbaked shell.
Mix cream, flour, sugar, almond and tapioca.
Pour over peaches. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Skin, bone and cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix spaghetti sauce mix with water and soy sauce and marinate 4 hours.
Cook chicken in lightly oiled frypan for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cut up green pepper, mushrooms and liquid from tomatoes and cook 2 minutes, covered.
Cut tomatoes in quarters; add to chicken and let warm.
Serve with rice.
Keep warm in low oven, uncovered.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Cook limas in a little salted water with butter.
Cook until tender (10 minutes).
Drain; save a little juice (separate).
Add onion, pimento and sour cream. Refrigerate overnight.
Add 1 tablespoon juice.
Heat and serve.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Add all ingredients together, one at a time, as listed.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: ham and cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and garlic until transparent.
Soak bread in milk.
Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mix beef, onions, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and eggs. Coarsely grate the cheese and set aside.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mushrooms.
Combine soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour over mushrooms and chicken.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Serve over rice.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add seasoning mix, water and salsa. Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread roll dough in large pie plate to form a crust.
Spoon on meat mixture.
Spread sour cream over meat. Cover with cheese slices.
Sprinkle over the 1/2 cup corn chips. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes and serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green pepper in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer tortillas which have been dipped in hot chicken stock long enough to soften.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Add in order: chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cartwheels
directions: Core apples leaving 1 1/4-inch diameter opening.
Place chocolate chips in blender or food processor until finely chopped. Mix remaining ingredients together and stuff core of apple.
Wrap each apple in plastic wrap and chill.
Slice thin before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
onions,	celery and hamburger in
skillet.
Pour off grease and add rice, mushrooms, soups and
water.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat until well mixed.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: two-bean ragout
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook the onion and garlic in the olive oil over low heat for about 6 minutes.
Stir in the jalapeno, chili powder and cumin; cook while stirring for about 1 minute.
Stir in the tomatoes, bring to a simmer and stir in the beans and broth.
Cover and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes. stir in the sugar and cook about 5 minutes more.
Season with salt.

title: spanish bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in food processor or tear by hand into small pieces.
Combine bread and eggs into one large bowl.
Then mix the remaining ingredients into the bowl.
Mix well!
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
When baking, be sure to put one pan of water and then the pan containing the mix, this will prevent the bottom and sides from burning.
You know when it's done by putting in a toothpick and it comes out clear.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut baked chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with cornbread.

title: rachel's favorite punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together juices and carbonated beverage.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.
Yields 38 servings.

title: zucchini honey bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.	Stir in nuts.
Combine zucchini and rest of the ingredients.
Add to flour mixture stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 4x5 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.	Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put spinach in casserole dish, add soup mix.
Mix well.
Put pad of margarine into spinach.
Cut cream cheese into cubes and push into spinach.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice cooker shrimp pilaf (or crawfish)
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Add mushrooms, beef broth, salt, pepper and rice.
Put in rice cooker and stir in shrimp.
Turn cooker on and push button to cook.
It will be done when rice cooker goes off.
Delicious meal.
Serve with salad. Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: peach ambrosia
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Chill for at least 30 minutes. Just before serving, add coconut and spoon into sherbet glasses. Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: stuffed creole tomatoes
directions: Remove a 1/2-inch slice from top of each tomato and chop. Scoop out most of pulp and chop.
Put a little salt, pepper and sugar inside each tomato and turn upside down on paper towel to drain.

title: broccoli-chicken-rice casserole
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine, then saute onion, bell pepper and celery (until onion is clear).
Add Cheez Whiz, rice, chicken and broccoli.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soups; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: italian style minestrone
directions: To the boiling water, add all ingredients except the spaghetti.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then add the spaghetti. Continue to simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil or other before serving.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Bake in four layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool them.
Cut horizontally each layer. Stack them with coconut filling.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Chill, peel and grate into a large bowl.
Over low heat, combine 1/4 cup butter and cheese until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions and seasonings.
Pour over grated potatoes.
Stir to blend and put in casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: classic tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a medium saucepan. Let stand 1 minute.
Add tomato juice to remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Cool to room temperature.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Unmold onto a lettuce lined plate.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: kim chee
directions: Wash cabbage and cut into large pieces.
Add 1/2 cup salt to water.
Mix well and soak cabbage for 5 hours.
Wash and drain cabbage thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients into jar.
Cover and place in cool place for 2 or 3 days until pickled.
Makes 1 quart.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples, together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cool.
When ready to use, add raw, diced apples. Serves 6.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Roll or pat out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on medium heat until done.

title: spaghetti
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Boil water; add noodles.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Heat tomato sauce.
Add vegetables.
Pour over noodles.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Gradually drizzle in chocolate.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Chill 30 minutes.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hot punch for winter months
directions: Make a spiced tea by boiling together for 10 minutes 2 cups water, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Make a syrup using 2 cups of sugar and 2 cups water.
Mix the spiced tea, hot tea, syrup and grape juice.
Strain juice of lemons and oranges and add just before serving.
Serve hot.
Serves 35 and 50.

title: boiled egg
directions: Place
an
unbroken
egg in a paper drinking cup.
Fill the cup with
water and set it on a bed of coals.
Allow it to boil to your taste.
The cup won't burn.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream
butter
and
shortening and sugar.
Add molasses. Dissolve
soda in water.
Add to mixture.
Add spices, salt and soda water.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Chill dough.
Roll out thin
and
cut	or
roll in small balls and press on cookie sheet with fork.
Bake at 350° to 375° until set, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: You can use the dry powdered buttermilk.
Make 1 cup according to directions.
I add it to the flour mixture and use 1 cup water.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in the chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: pasadena burrito roll appetizer
directions: Place tortilla on working surface and spread with beans and rest of ingredients through green chiles.
Roll up and wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Slice into 1-inch rounds and serve with guacamole and salsa.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash crosswise and cook with onion until tender; drain.
Mix together dressing and melted oleo.
Put half the dressing in bottom of casserole.
Save remainder for top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, spices and salt together. Toss nuts and raisins lightly into flour mixture.
Beat sugar and oil together with mixer at low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add pumpkin.
Add flour mixture and water.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise, horseradish and shrimp and pat into a ball.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Pour cocktail sauce over ball and serve with crackers.

title: party punch
directions: Mix sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice in advance. Add ginger ale and sherbet before serving.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix.
Separate dough into 4 squares.
Press perforations together to seal.
Put 1/2 cup mixture onto each square.
Seal.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients, except onions.
Pour into a greased casserole. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: jerry's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for 24 hours.

title: new york style vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill until thickened.

title: pineapple arkansas cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage and carrots fine.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, milk and vinegar and pour over cabbage and carrots.
Stir mixture; chill and serve.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, chocolate, salt and 2 Tbsp. butter thoroughly. Stir constantly until candy comes to a boil, then stir no more. Lower heat and cook slowly.
When candy reaches 240° on a candy thermometer, cook about 8 to 10 minutes longer or until a drop of fudge in cold water forms a soft ball.
Add remaining butter and cool by placing pan in cold water.
Beat until creamy (as it creams the candy will lose its sheen).
Add vanilla and nuts and mix well. Pour into buttered 8x8 inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: rugalah
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter together.
Add salt, flour and sugar.
Chill until firm.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll out each into rectangle 4-inches wide.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, raisins, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll into log and brush top with cinnamon and sugar.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: katie schaffer's corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown and wooden pick inserted near center comes out clear.
To make this taste more like Grandma Schaffer's, bake in a preheated cast-iron skillet. Grandma made her corn bread on top of the stove using a preheated omelet pan (low flame 10 minutes each side).
Serve warm with sorghum for a down home treat in the morning.

title: cherry-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Beat all ingredients on medium speed for 45 seconds except cherries.
Stir in cherries and pour into pan.
Bake 70 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Immediately loosen and remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: golden mushroom fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, mushrooms, onion, pimiento, salt and celery seed.
Mix egg yolk and sour cream and stir into mushroom mixture.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Gently fold into mushroom mixture.
In heavy saucepan or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Transfer to rack to drain.
Serve hot.
Makes 12.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Note:
Double this recipe for full size cake pan.

title: black beans and brown rice
directions: Saute in sprayed skillet with a little water: onion, peppers and garlic.
Add beans and liquid.
Simmer until desired consistency, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add a few drops hot sauce and to taste.
Or add cumin if desired.
Serve beans over cooked rice with hot sauce.

title: mexicali-chicken casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9x13 casserole dish.
Layer ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Microwave 15 minutes.) Serve 12 to 15.

title: mustard fish
directions: Dip fish pieces in mustard and sour cream mix.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Chill 15 minutes in refrigerator and fry.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook together first 7 ingredients until zucchini is tender. Beat eggs and fold in shredded cheese, then mix into zucchini. Line 10-inch pie pan with 8 ounce package crescent rolls.
Spread crust with 2 teaspoons mustard.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: ants on a log
directions: Wash and cut leaves off celery.
Cut celery stalks in desired length.
Spread on peanut butter or cream cheese.
Sprinkle on raisins.

title: comfort frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar gradually; beat until stiff.
Make syrup of rest of ingredients; boil to soft ball stage.
Add syrup to egg whites slowly.
Add vanilla.
Set aside to cool.
Beat until stiff enough to put on cake.
If icing gets hard, add few drops of hot water.

title: friendship cup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 2 minutes; dot with butter.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients except rye bread in medium bowl until creamy.
Pack into 2-cup crock or non-metal container; cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours, no longer than 2 weeks. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with snipped chives if desired.
Serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: In large bowl, prepare dressing mix and place in refrigerator to thicken.
Arrange crescent rolls in bottom of pan to form crust. Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Combine artichokes, cheese and pimentos with the Ranch dressing.
Pour over crescent roll crust. Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted, approximately 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Boil butter, cocoa, oil and water.
Pour liquid mixture over sugar and flour; beat on low.
Add eggs, butter, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in oblong pan.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix together.
Add sour cream and marshmallows.
Chill. Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 9 ungreased pan at 350° until done.

title: spicy braunschweiger spread(great for parties)
directions: Blend all ingredients well by hand and chill several hours. Do not use blender.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pour Egg Beaters on pizza crust. Cut ham and bacon in small pieces and put on top of pizza; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and refrigerate, preferably overnight.
May be placed in decorative mold and unmolded for presentation
or
served
by
the spoonful right from the dish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Put in fruit, sweetened to taste.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle almond extract over peaches. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can substitute 1 cup blueberries for peaches, in that case, omit almond extract.

title: microwave tea
directions: Microwave on High power for 3 1/2 minutes to just below boiling.
Take out of microwave, cover and let set for 5 minutes. Pour into gallon container with sugar to taste or sweetener.
Fill container with cold water.

title: sweet dough(takes 60 minutes.)
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm in medium-size saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt and sugar. Crumble the yeast into mixture. Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Mix in the egg and soft shortening.
Mix in Gold Medal flour (just enough to handle easily).
Mix dough with hands until moderately stiff.
Turn out on floured board and knead several times until smooth.
Shape for Cinnamon Swirls.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Mix together pasta, reserved juice and remaining ingredients, except pineapple and broccoli.
Arrange pineapple and broccoli around pasta.
Cover and chill.
Toss before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: genuine fig preserves
directions: Wash well select ripe firm figs.
It is not necessary to peel figs and the stems may be left. Cover the bottom of a large enamel (white) boiler with a layer of sugar.
Put a layer of figs on top of this.
Alternate the layers until the figs and sugar are used up, ending with a layer of sugar.
Be sure sugar covers all the figs.
Put a cover on boiler and put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine or butter in an 8 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder together, then add milk.
Pour this over melted margarine or butter.
Put fruit and juice over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until golden brown.
Yields about 9 servings.

title: raspberry ring
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water, add frozen raspberries, stir till thawed, chill till partly set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Rub brown crumbs from cake and tear in bit size pieces.
Place half in 10 inch tube pan, pour half Jello mixture over cake, repeat once more with cake bits and Jello.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, sugar and brown sugar with milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Combine beans with celery, onions and green peppers.
Blend together vinegar, water, sugar and salt. Heat to boil.
Pour over mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: veggie appetizer pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Press crescent rolls onto pan; form edges.
Bake for 9-10 minutes (don't let it brown).
Let cool. Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and dry salad dressing mix.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled crust and top with vegetables and cheese.
Press down lightly and chill for at least 1 hour.
Cut into pieces.
(Don't make this too much in advance as crust becomes soggy if allowed to sit for very long.)

title: soda bread(raisin)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add raisins.
Melt shortening.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk in separate bowl. Combine just until flour is moistened.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Grease and flour top of pan.
Slit dough.

title: mushroom wine sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until onion turns yellow. Add mushrooms; saute approximately 5 minutes.
Add flour; stir and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add bouillon and wine.
Stir and simmer for a few minutes.
May be used over chopped sirloin steak, hamburger steaks, sliced London broils, etc.

title: cottage potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Cool, peel and dice. Place in large mixing bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except cornflakes, and stir until well mixed.
Place in a large casserole.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange parfait
directions: Use a 2 quart bowl.
Microwave marshmallows on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
They will puff up.
Add orange juice and beat with wire whip.
Juice and marshmallows should be smoothly blended together. Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Pour into parfait or dessert dishes and chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with orange slices and a sprig of fresh mint if available.
It's good in a graham cracker pie crust.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and scallop pilaf
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in turmeric or saffron.
Add rice, onion, green or red pepper and garlic; cook for approximately 3 minutes, until rice and onion are translucent, stirring often.
Pour in chicken broth and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer 13 minutes.
Add scallops, shrimp and peas.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes, or until shrimp is pink, scallops are opaque and peas are heated through.
Season to taste and serve.

title: pasta with vegetable sauce
directions: Brown lightly, garlic, onion and eggplant.
Add Italian tomatoes, cut fine.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.

title: venison loaf
directions: About 2 hours before serving, cook onion in skillet over medium heat
in butter.
Add celery and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly and stir in bread crumbs, milk, salt and thyme leaves.
Add venison, ground beef and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake meat loaf in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off pan juices.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 10 servings, about 215 calories per serving.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Melt margarine in large heavy saucepan.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Cook for about 10 minutes until onions are clear.
Add flour and blend well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stir often.
Add parsley and shrimp, cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add half & half and cheese, mix well.
Add salt, pepper.
Cook covered on low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring often.
While waiting for the sauce to finish cooking, in another pot boil noodles. Drain and add noodles to sauce mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a 10x12 buttered glass dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes. Serves 12-14.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together the cheese, about 3/4 of the pineapple, pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Add about 3/4 of the pecans.
Form into a ball (it will be soft).
Chill until firm and then roll in the remaining pecans.
Serve with Triscuits or other small crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and add to remaining ingredients.
Mix and add 1 cup sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate. Keeps several days.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and brown sugar in bowl until fluffy. Beat in pumpkin, eggs and evaporated milk.
Add cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg; beat well.
Pour into crusts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until edge is set. Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla in small bowl.
Spread over surface of warm cheesecake.
Return to 350° oven and bake for 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter soup
directions: Saute the onion in the peanut oil, until tender.
Add the flour, celery salt and salt.
Blend in the peanut butter.
Add the milk gradually, stirring to blend.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Add the tomato juice; bring to a boil.
Serves 4.

title: jalapeno cheese pie(aka texas fudge)
directions: Sprinkle jalapeno pepper in a greased 1-quart ring mold (or 9-inch pan with glass in center).
Spread grated cheese over peppers.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Pour over cheese.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, rotating every 2 minutes.
Turn out immediately.
Enjoy!

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Finely chop carrots.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook or steam carrots; drain.
Slice onions very thin.
In blender mix all remaining ingredients.
Place carrots in a bowl. Top with onions.
Cover with sauce mixture and place in refrigerator at least 12 hours prior to serving.

title: rice with dates and almonds
directions: Put the water on to boil; dash of salt in water.
Put the rice in boiling water; cover and turn fire low and cook 20 minutes or until the rice is done.
Simmer the cut dates in butter a few minutes.
Saute almonds in another pan in butter until they are a little brown.
Add the almonds and dates to the rice and serve.

title: jam cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together and add flour.
Roll into 1-inch snake and refrigerate.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Make a dent with your thumb and dab jam into hole.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread mixture over cooled cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
In a small bowl, combine marmalade and water; blend well and spread over fruit.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour 3 times with salt.
Add, alternating with sour cream to which soda has been added.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and almond extract.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: just-like-boxed brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and you will have a doughy substance. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cheese, eggs and sugar.
Spread this on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° until cake springs back when pressed lightly.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Place above ingredients in a mixing bowl.
In blender, put 6 to 8 very ripe peaches, peeled.
Sweeten to taste with approximately 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend well with other ingredients. Pour into freezer container.
Finish filling container with milk. Freeze.

title: b~b~q baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 326 uncovered for 2 hours; stir after the 1st hour.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and egg yolks. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer cake, Cool Whip mixture and Butterfingers; layer twice.

title: red cabbage cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage half in two and cut out core.
Shred cabbage in a food processor or with a large knife and place cabbage in a large bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup vinegar into a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour it over cabbage and toss quickly until well mixed. Whisk mustard with remaining 3 tablespoons of vinegar and salt and pepper to taste in a medium bowl.
Whisk in oil.
Add dressing to cabbage gradually, tossing.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
A short time before serving, add chopped scallions to salad.
Serve sprinkled with toasted walnuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick and easy beef stew
directions: In a bowl, mix together the soup mix, mushroom soup and wine. Place meat in a deep baking dish or electric skillet and pour sauce over it.
Bake, covered, at 350° or simmer in an electric skillet at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: potato salad (white potatoes)(makes about 18 servings)
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until cooked.
Remove outer skin and dice potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir in onion, relish, celery, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: blue ribbon chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix flour into mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: never-fail popovers(makes 6 large or 12 small)
directions: Break eggs into bowl. Stir remaining ingredients into eggs with a spoon until just blended.
Pour into six copiously buttered custard cups or 12 muffin tins (fill about 3/4 full).
Put into cold oven, then turn on heat to 450°.
Bake exactly 1/2 hour with no peeking.
Remove from oven, puncture necks of popovers in several places with a sharp knife.
Return to oven with heat off for 10 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and grind peppers and onions.
Pour boiling water over the mixture and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain. Pour cold water over and let stand 4 minutes.
Can use more green peppers and red peppers for color.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, peppers and onions; bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Good and easy.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed. Drain. In 9 x 13 dish, layer macaroni. Sprinkle 1/2 shredded cheese and 1/2 crackers. After second layer, add milk until it is at the top of your baking dish. Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in melted butter until tender.
Whisk in flour, mixing well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Gradually add chicken stock and cream; heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and stir until melted.
Place broccoli and chicken or turkey slices in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread with heavy cream, whipped, and top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Place in broiler until browned.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, sour cream and sugar together.
Put layer (half) mixture, then layer of nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put remaining batter on, then more nut mixture on top. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and cool. Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Then bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale just before serving. Makes 1 3/4 gallons.

title: nana's spinach soup
directions: Boil until vegetables are done.
Puree in blender.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Add more boiling water to make 1 gallon of soup.
Add beef bouillon cubes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice 3 bananas.
Dip in lemon juice and drain. Arrange on bottom of prepared crust.
Pour filling over bananas. Cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and oil.
Add all other ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto sheet of heavy aluminum foil.
Flatten slightly with hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until slightly browned.
Makes 100 to 120 cookies.

title: seafood mold
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot soup.
Combine with the cream cheese and beat with electric beater until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients, except crackers.
Pack lightly in oiled mold and chill.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: fluffy pink punch
directions: In a punch bowl, stir together cranberry juice, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Spoon sherbet into the punch bowl by tablespoonfuls; stir just until combined. Slowly pour ginger ale down the side of bowl.
Stir gently until combined.
Serve immediately.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix first onions, ground meat and oil in iron skillet.
Add the rest into skillet.
Heat, stirring, for a little, then put skillet in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake in greased dish at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: spanish roast
directions: Combine vinegar, Worcestershire, ketchup, chili powder, paprika, pepper and water; bring to boil and remove from heat. Salt roast to taste, then braise on both sides in hot fat.
Place in a roasting pan on a piece of foil large enough to cover.
Top with hot sauce and onions.
Seal foil and bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender, basting frequently with the sauce.

title: potato cakes
directions: Drain tuna fish.
Add potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
Fry until golden brown.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Stir together and drop onto a lined, greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
After baking, sprinkle with sugar crystals.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, molasses and water thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400° (moderate heat).
Drop dough by teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Cookies will spread slightly during baking.
Bake about 8 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Makes about 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: peppermint patties
