directions: Rub softened butter into the sugar. Add milk, vanilla and salt and mix thoroughly. The more you work it, the better. Work peppermint flavoring and a little green food coloring into the mixture. Form into small patties; chill.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers and vinegar in blender.
Place other ingredients in pan and boil for 4 minutes; then add food coloring.
Pour in sterile jars and seal.
Serve with cream cheese on crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf.
Pour second can of tomato sauce over top of loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: pound cake(serving size:  10)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 8 1/2-inch Pyrex loaf dish with Pam (or use individual small loaf pans).
Cream the butter with sugar on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Add extract.
Measure and then sift flour.
Add 1 egg and then a little flour, beating 2 minutes.
Add second egg and half of remaining flour and beat 2 minutes.
Add sour cream, rest of flour and extract, beating 2 minutes.
Spread batter evenly in dish.
Bake for 65 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Remove from dish.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Be sure to slice before freezing loaf.
Thaw to use.
Use within 6 months.

title: fast and easy chicken and casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Beat together cottage cheese, eggs and sour cream.
Add flour, salt and sugar.
Beat batter until it becomes thick and creamy. Fry the pancakes in buttered skillet.
Serve with maple syrup, jelly or preserves.

title: crispy tuna balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flake crumbs and mix well. Shape into small balls and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Fry in hot deep oil (375°) until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
These appetizers can be frozen up to 6 weeks and reheated for 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Spray a 3-quart rectangular baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Sprinkle with chili peppers and Cheddar cheese; set aside.

title: bean ham soup
directions: In large pot, heat beans to boiling; chop onions and add to beans.
Add salt and ham bone.
Cover and boil gently, 1 to 2 1/2 hours or until beans are soft and ham is tender.
Remove bone; add meat from bone to beans along with remaining ingredients; cook until tender.
Serve.

title: baked chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chopped beef. Wrap 1/2 strip bacon around each half chicken breast.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken breast.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 hours and uncovered for 1 hour.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwave bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly on crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes until chocolate is firm and add bananas. Pour milk in large bowl and pudding mix.
Beat for 1 minute with wire whisk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust. Spread with whipped topping.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel and cook squash for 20 to 25 minutes.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add mushrooms and saute along with onions. Chop cooked squash in 1/2-inch cubes.
Put in colander and drain well.
Chop cheese slices in 1/8-inch squares.
Crumble bread and combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bread pieces.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in unbaked crust until it tests done with a kitchen knife.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Congeal.
Then spread sour cream over top of salad.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts (if desired).

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; set aside, retaining liquid.
Brown onion in oil. Add vegetables; barely cover with water.
Add clam juice.
Simmer until tender.
In a 5-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add flour, then half and half to make a white sauce.
Add clams, vegetables in their broths and seasonings.
Simmer.

title: artichoke-asparagus casserole
directions: Place layers of artichokes and asparagus in 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in glass or enamel double boiler.
Heat until bubbly.
Do not boil.
Pour over casserole. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer all ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popped popcorn in a lightly greased bowl.
Combine other ingredients in pan and boil.
Pour over popcorn; cool.
Butter your hands and form popcorn syrup into balls.
Wrap in wax paper. Can also be wrapped in colored cellophane paper and hung on Christmas trees.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Add flour to ingredients to make soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps for 4 or 5 days.
Take out amounts as needed. Let rise until double and bake until brown.

title: ruth's coffee cake
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite-size pieces. Put 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish. Crumble raw hamburger over cabbage. Add onions, rice and tomatoes. Cover with remaining cabbage and seasoning. Pour tomato soup and water over top. Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours in 400° oven. ENJOY.

title: chicken mushroom lasagna
directions: In large skillet on medium-high heat, saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon oil until golden, stirring often, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium-low; add garlic and parsley and saute 2 minutes more.
Do not let garlic brown.

title: it's the snap in your beans
directions: Zap prepared dressing in cruet (without cap) on High for 30 seconds.
Cruet may be hot.
Pour over hot cooked vegetables.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Add shrimp and stir to blend. Serve with crackers or potato chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat.
Add water to cover.
Add onion slices.
Put spices in cheesecloth and tie or use a large tea ball.
Add remaining brown sugar, salt, vinegar and bay leaves.
Cook slowly over medium heat 3 to 4 hours.
Take meat out.
Add to juices 1/2 cup brown sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Be sure to remove pickling spice bag.
Thicken gravy with flour and water mixture.
Slice meat and add to gravy.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Combine corned beef (crumbled), cheese, soup, onions, milk and mushrooms.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: no-bake cool whip cheesecake
directions: Whip softened cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar and Cool Whip. Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make 1/4-inch cracker crust or two 9-inch pie crusts.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust. Top with fruit. Refrigerate until served.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the boiling water and small marshmallows, then add the cold water, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Top with mixture of the egg, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Add the butter; cool.
Add the cream cheese, added to Dream Whip.

title: apple cheesecake pie
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon orange rind, cinnamon, nutmeg, orange juice and butter in large saucepan; bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add apples and simmer just until tender and translucent, about 8 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into apple mixture.
Cook, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature. Spoon into baked pie shell.
Whip the cream cheese until fluffy; gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon orange rind.
Beat in egg.
Spoon over apples; top with almonds and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden. Chill before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: spareribs kinsale
directions: Cut spareribs in serving size pieces.
Remove excess fat. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over spareribs.
Let stand 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: grape jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 qt batter bowl and microwave 15 to 18 minutes on high, or until jelly leaves a coating on a spoon dipped into the mixture. It will thicken more as it cools. Pour into glasses. Cover with plastic wrap and store in refrigerator. Jars can be sterilized in the normal manner, filled with the hot jelly and sealed.

title: molded beet aspic
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix in all ingredients, except beets and celery.
Chill until partially set.
Add vegetables; chill until firm.
Serves 6 (makes 1 quart).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg and vanilla in small mixer bowl on medium speed until smooth, about 1 minute. Stir in apple and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve warm.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Put in serving bowl. Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve on Melba rounds.

title: korean marinade-barbecue(or pul ko ki)
directions: Mix ingredients together, except meat.
Marinate meat in sauce at least 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
You can bake, broil or barbecue!

title: beer-cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions; cook until they just begin to wilt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour gradually. Stir in broth, milk, beer, cheese and Worcestershire.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the soup comes to a boil. Serves 6.

title: black skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa until well blended. Melt butter in iron skillet. Add dry ingredients, and mix lightly. Beat egg yolks until lemon colored then add milk and beat. Add egg mixture to skillet gradually stirring constantly. Cook slowly until thickened. Add vanilla.

title: peanut butter crisps or sticks
directions: Cut bread (with crusts) into 5 strips each (stale bread works well).
Place in single layer on baking sheet and dry in 200° oven
for
hours.
Mix
peanut oil, peanut butter and sugar together.
Dip
bread sticks into mixture, then roll in graham cracker
or
vanilla
wafer
crumbs.
Place
on baking sheet. Bake
in
200° oven 10 minutes and leave in oven until oven
is completely	cool,
preferably
overnight.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare white cake mix and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare jello.
Mix jello with 3/4 cup boiling water; add 1/2 cup cold water.
Poke holes in cake with large fork.
Pour jello in holes.
Make sure you cover cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil, skimming top occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve sugar, Kool-Aid and water.
Mix everything together and freeze until ready to serve.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
Drop biscuits by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450° or until brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush on warm biscuits.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and cocoa.
Cool.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs, flour, baking soda and salt to date mixture.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 package chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pinto bean - sausage stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large cooking pot.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Yields 12 cups.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.

title: hobo packs
directions: Shape hamburger into 2 patties (1/2 pound each). Place on separate sheets of aluminum foil large enough to wrap completely. Divide all other ingredients in half, placing on top of hamburger patty. Completely wrap in aluminum foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Carefully unwrap. Very hot!

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: In a small amount of butter, saute spinach, bread crumbs, cheese and wine.
Fill mushroom caps and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato and feta cheese
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
Cut tomatoes into wedges. In large bowl, combine tomatoes, olive oil or salad oil, marjoram, red wine vinegar, salt, sugar and coarsely ground pepper.
Gently stir to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let rise for 1 hour.
Pour out on floured board, roll thin as noodles.
Spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on high until candy melts.
Turn on low to keep hot; serve.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a beater until fluffy. Serve with bite size pieces of fruit to be dipped in the fruit dip.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Bring beans to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add other ingredients and simmer until done, then salt to taste.
Additional water may be needed during cooking.
Soup thickens as it cools.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 quarts.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add next three ingredients and cook until oyster edges begin to curl.
Add oyster juice and cream. Serve with spoonful of butter on top and dash of paprika.

title: potato cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion, dill and thyme in oil.
Add cauliflower, potato and stock.
Cover and cook until tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in blender.
(I use 2 cups measuring cup as a scoop and blend 2 cups at a time, pouring mixture right back into the pot.)
Repeat until all large pieces are blended.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and season hamburger, drain. Put into 9x13 inch cake pan. Layer tater tots on top of hamburger. Next, layer the can of soup on top of Tater Tots. Next layer grated cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 45-60 minutes. Uncover and bake 10-15 minutes longer. Serve and enjoy.

title: baked cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt, pepper and cream.
Put cabbage in casserole dish that has been lightly sprayed with Pam. Pour cream mixture over cabbage.
Take 6 slices Canadian bacon and lay on top of mixture or if using regular bacon, enough to cover over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick chicken cutlets romano
directions: Fork whip egg and oil together in a shallow bowl.
Place the flour in another shallow bowl.
Dip the cutlets first in the flour, then in the egg mixture and then again in the flour. Arrange the coated cutlets on a nonstick cookie sheet.
Place in a very hot 450° oven and bake 6 minutes on each side.

title: quick and easy mashed potatoes
directions: Combine water and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from heat and stir in potato flakes.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cover and keep warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put in jar and keep in refrigerator.

title: frozen peanut butter-banana sandwiches(children's snack)
directions: In small bowl, blend peanut butter and honey.
Spread about 1 tablespoon mixture on each of 10 crackers.
Top with banana slices and remaining crackers.
Freeze for at least 1 hour.
Individually wrap and store in freezer for up to 1 week.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops; place in shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with celery, lemon juice, brown sugar and seasoning.
Pour tomato sauce and water over chops.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven until tender.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Salt chicken and roll in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot oil. Remove oil from pan.
Place chicken back in pan.
Pour mushroom soup and water over chicken and cook until tender.

title: peppermint meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Line two cookie sheets with foil.
With an electric mixer, beat the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Beat in sugar a little at a time until mixture is smooth, shiny and very stiff, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets (or pipe with pastry bag and star tip) close together.
Sprinkle crushed candy canes over tops.
Bake 1 hour, then turn off oven. Open oven door slightly and let meringues cool.
Store in covered containers in a dry place.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and water in a 2-quart pan.
Stir to dissolve sugar and bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add maple flavoring.
Yields 32 ounces.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and vanilla bark over low heat in double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed thoroughly, then pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Will take at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours to firm.
Ready to eat for freeze.
Freezes really good.

title: velvet supreme
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, nuts and margarine and bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9 inch glass pan.
Let cool.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Scrape carrots and grate coarsely.
Add raisins and mix.
Mix mayonnaise, honey, vinegar and cinnamon and mix good.
Pour over carrots and toss.
Let marinate at least 2 hours before serving. Will keep one week.

title: jello pudding pops
directions: Mix together until smooth and slightly thickened.
Pour into paper cups and place popsicle sticks into center.
Freeze and enjoy.
Great for picnics.
Use one and three pound coffee cans with ice and rock salt.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Divide everything into thirds.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Put 1/3 cake in punch bowl.
Layer with pudding, pineapple, cherries, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat these directions twice.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together and pour into crust.
Chill about an hour.

title: wassle
directions: Wrap spices in cloth and tie up.
Simmer in crock-pot all day.

title: krispie peanut clusters
directions: In microwave, melt bark and chips together.
Remove and stir. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or into paper candy cups.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: pea soup
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce and simmer 15 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Transfer in small batches to blender; blend until smooth. Transfer back to pan and stir in sour cream. Serve hot; garnish with mint, if desired.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands in large bowl. Shape meat loaf in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour ketchup on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: Heat; simmer the Cheddar soup and Ro-Tel until creamy and smooth.
Serve with any kind of chips.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Put in freezer until syrupy.
Beat until frothy, then add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until served.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Bring cherries and juice to a boil.
Add dry gelatin and sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple with juice and chopped nuts.
Pour into mold or bowl and chill until set.

title: "cousin carrie's" pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at least 1 minute each.
Add dry ingredients, starting with flour, then milk and ending with flour.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Cool to room temperature.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in oblong dish and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 12.

title: bagna calda hot dip (italian)
directions: Melt butter with olive oil in a small pan, preferably Earthenware.
Saute garlic until light brown.
Don't let it scorch.
Add anchovies and mash with the back of a wooden spoon. Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook until hot, 3 or 4 minutes.
Serve in a fondue pot with bread sticks, celery, strips of green peppers, cabbage or any vegetables as dippers.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls; flatten with a glass.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: souper stuffed cheeseburgers
directions: In large bowl, combine soup mix, ground beef and water. Shape into 12 patties.
Place 2 tablespoons cheese in center of 6 patties.
Top with remaining patties and seal edges tightly. Grill or broil until done, about 12 minutes.
Serve on sesame rolls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon drop zucchini relish
directions: Shred squash with peel on and turned toward grating surface. "Ball Bat" size works great if peel is still soft.
Scrape out the seeds.
Shred or chop fine onions.
Mix well zucchini, onion and salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse well with cold water and drain.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender. Peel and slice thinly. Put in a baking dish. Cover with butter slices and 1/2 box brown sugar. Sprinkle cinnamon over brown sugar. Mix eggs, sugar, flour, milk and vanilla in mixing bowl. Mix well. Pour over potatoes and bake at 425° until brown.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening and peanut butter.
Mix together until it resembles coarse meal, then add corn syrup and milk.
Form into long roll about 2 inches in diameter and wrap in wax paper.
Chill dough until firm.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place half of dough slices, about 2 inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Dab center of each slice with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter (plain or crunchy). Top with another slice of dough.
Seal 2 slices with prongs of fork.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes or until done.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: gourmet goulash
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and brown meat.
Add onions; saute lightly.
Stir in salt and pepper, flour and paprika.
Add wine, sour cream and tomato sauce, stirring to blend smoothly.
Turn the mixture into a casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Add all other ingredients but zucchini.
Simmer until flavored.
Peel and slice zucchini; remove seeds.
Place zucchini into a large cake pan and cover with hamburger.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Remove from oven and cover with slices of cheese.
Serve once the cheese is melted.

title: caraway-fruit quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 5 by 9 inch loaf pan. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir in caraway seeds.
Add butter.
With a pastry blender or two knives, blend until mixture is the texture of coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins, currants, and walnuts.
Blend beaten eggs and milk; add all at once to fruit mixture, stirring just until all the flour is moistened.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead lightly until smooth; shape into smooth loaf.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake for one hour, or until loaf starts to come away from pan. Yields one 5 by 9 inch loaf.

title: lime ice cream salad
directions: Thoroughly drain crushed pineapple.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling jello and stir until dissolved.
Blend in the ice cream; chill until partially congealed.
Fold in grated cheese, drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil. Place the potatoes in a well-greased casserole dish. Pour the boiling liquid over the potatoes. Bake 45 minutes in a 375° preheated oven. (About 2/3 of potatoes should be in or covered by liquid mixture.)

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Add all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour melted marshmallows over these ingredients and mix by hand; press in waxed paper container. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed on mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: custard pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and blend. Add vanilla and milk; mix and pour into unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle top with 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake about 25 minutes more.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 stick oleomargarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine and beat 15 minutes. Spread over crust.
Slice bananas onto filling, add pineapple and then cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on nuts and cherries.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite sliced apples.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Stir oil, dressing, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Pour over broken pretzels.
Let this all soak together about 1 hour, stirring occasionally, so each pretzel is well coated.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Stir the pretzels on the cookie sheet.
Turn the heat down to 325° and bake 5 minutes more.
Take out of the oven and stir well.
Let the pretzels cool well.
Store in airtight containers or bags.

title: baked chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onion; add the remaining ingredients and bake on a long flat pan for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Add Chinese noodles on top when about ready to serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add to crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: friday special tuna
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with peas or a gelatin salad.
Serves four.

title: spinach salad
directions: In small frying pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Do not drain. In a 1-cup measure, place raw egg, sugar, vinegar and enough water to make 3/4 cup.
Pour over bacon and grease.
Cook, stirring constantly, until dressing thickens.
Season to taste.
Mix the greens and onion.
Pour hot dressing over greens; toss.
Garnish with egg slices.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack into greased 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Lightly beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Turn into pans and bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes (with glass loaf pans, bake at 325°).

title: texas firecrackers
directions: Select 24 (2-inch long) salad peppers; set others aside for garnish. Remove and discard stems and seeds from peppers; drain thoroughly on paper towels. Stuff each pepper with 1 piece Monterey Jack cheese and 1 piece of chicken; set aide.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Top with 2 strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.

title: leftover turkey pie
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish with butter generously.
Cook first four ingredients together.
Mix Bisquick, flour, parsley and margarine together.
Beat eggs; season with salt and pepper and mix with leftover mashed potatoes.
Add to Bisquick mixture and work together.
Mixture will be sticky.
Spoon mixture into dish and using the back of spoon, pat it into bottom and sides of dish. Save some mixture for top.
Put cold turkey, gravy and peas in dish; add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Put more turkey and gravy in center.
Spoon Bisquick mixture around sides, sealing well.
Let circle in center open.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: honey
directions: Cut meat in chunks.
Pack clean, hot jars with meat and add 1 teaspoon coarse salt to each jar.
Put hot lid on and add ring and tighten.
Bring back 1/2 turn and cold pack in water for 3 hours. Tighten lids and put away.
Add 1 slice of onion in each jar if desired.

title: old fashioned hash
directions: In large skillet, melt shortening.
Cook onion in shortening until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until well browned, about 10 minutes.
Turn and brown other side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fat free dairy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 cup.
Absolutely fat free.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
margarine.
Mix
all
other
ingredients. Bake in square cake pan
at 325° for about 25 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Mix vegetables and chicken.
Place evenly in dish.
Mix soup, broth and pepper; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Combine baking mix, milk and margarine in separate bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Spread evenly 2/3 of batter into cookie or jelly roll pan.
Top with lemon filling. Spread evenly.
Drop by teaspoonful the rest of the batter. Scatter across top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: baked-barbecued shrimp
directions: Head shrimp.
Wash and drain.
Line bottom of flat pan with shrimp.
Melt butter; add salt, pepper, garlic powder, lemon juice, oregano and crab boil.
Pour over shrimp and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake or shells will stick to shrimp.
May be prepared in microwave, but must be stirred frequently so all the shrimp cook evenly.
Serve with tossed salad, French bread and large, absorbent napkins.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Sprinkle
the
nuts
and
coconut
in
the
bottom of a greased 9
x 13-inch pan. Mix the chocolate cake mix, pudding, eggs, vanilla,
oil
and
water
and
pour	over
the nuts and coconut mixture.
Mix the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread
over the cake dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center of cake springs back.

title: chili without beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add seasonings to taste (more for spicy, less for milder taste).
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add all remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Adjust seasoning if necessary for your taste and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour longer.
Adjust thickness with small can of V-8 juice for desired consistency.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place potatoes and onion in baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, cheese, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Add broth.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken breasts oriental
directions: Mix sweet and sour sauce, onion soup and cranberry sauce in a bowl.
Pour over chicken breasts in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef, cooked rice, chopped onion, salt, pepper and egg together.
Trim off thickest part of stem from cabbage leaves. Divide meat into equal portions.
Wrap each portion in a leaf. Fasten with toothpicks.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters. Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Dip oysters in egg mixture and roll in crumbs or corn meal. Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper. Serve immediately with slices of lemon and tartar sauce.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Add other ingredients, mix all together with spoon.
Bake in loaf pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: artichoke soup
directions: Drain artichokes from marinade.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons of oil; save for salad dressing.
Put the rest of the marinade in a saucepan; add the celery and onion.
Saute until slightly brown. Then add the water and crushed bouillon.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir the cornstarch and salt into the half and half and then add to the mixture.
Cook, while stirring, until mixture boils and begins to thicken.
Cut the larger artichokes in half. Add to the mixture and heat.

title: fat-free and guilt-free lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Heat oil.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add mushrooms and carrots.
Stir in olives, tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover bottom of baking dish with sauce.
Then layer noodles, cottage cheese, spinach/broccoli, 1/3 of the cheeses and sauce.
Repeat and end with noodles.
You can put remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese on top of noodles.
Cook for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Bon appetit!

title: prince of wales cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with spices, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately in thirds with buttermilk, beating smooth after each addition. Grease two 8-inch cake pans.
Pour batter in pans.
Bake at 375° (you may have to adjust oven heat to 350°) for 30 minutes.
Take layers out of pans and cool thoroughly on cake racks.
Assemble layers together with Lemon Filling and frost with Boiled Icing.

title: french stew
directions: Mix all together and put in large roaster.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and set aside.
Shred cheese and set aside.
Mix cornmeal, corn, eggs, milk, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add most of bacon grease.
In a 10-inch iron skillet, pour 2 tablespoons of bacon grease, put in half the batter.
Put meat on top, add cheese, onion and pepper.
Put other half batter on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and cheese.
Fold in eggs.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and peppers.
Put in a large greased casserole or 2 small square pans.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.
Pan should be large enough so that grits servings will be 1 1/2 inches thick.
These are good for breakfast too.

title: cherry-blueberry delight
directions: Press into pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes (check after 10 minutes to make sure it doesn't get too brown).
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: wild rice and chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in large oval baking dish with lid.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika.
Bake covered for 90 minutes or until done at 350°. Serves 6.

title: german-style kolaches
directions: Let shortening dissolve in hot milk.
Cool until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sprinkle sugar over yeast in mixing bowl.
Mix salt, eggs, milk and shortening mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sugar in small bowl, then add yeast (yeast can be foamy now).
Add all together, flour a little at a time, until all used up.
Work dough with hands until glossy.
Cover; let rise about 1 hour in a warm place.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Drop dough, teaspoon size, onto floured board.
Roll in ball on cookie sheet.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Brush with butter; bake for 30 minutes.
Put fruit in center before baking.

title: salsa
directions: In small saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes.
Serve warm with hamburgers, fish, tacos, tostadas or tortilla chips.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken au vin
directions: Cook chicken, cut in pieces.
Cook noodles in broth, adding a little nutmeg.
Mix garlic, soup, cream, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise and wine; set aside.
Place noodles in bottom of casserole; put chicken on top.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, almonds and mushrooms over top.
Sprinkle chopped parsley on top.
Bake in large casserole for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: leftover pie
directions: In large skillet, put vegetable oil, celery and onion.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Add diced meat, heat and stir.
Add veggies and optional stuffing or potato.
Stir in cream of chicken soup or the gravy.
Heat through, stirring often.
Turn into a pie plate. Place pie crust on top.
Flute the edges.
Put a few small slits on top of crust to vent.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Bring to a soft boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter (more or less than 1 cup can be added to suit your taste).
Stir until thick.
Put in a buttered pan. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: cheese and ham quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry shell and bake 7 minutes. Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Sprinkle ham and cheeses into partially-baked shell.
In medium bowl, beat eggs until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour over cheeses.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover edges of pie shell with tinfoil while baking the second time to avoid too dark edges.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes; cut into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: salmon steaks with asparagus
directions: Arrange fish in 10-inch skillet; sprinkle with salt and rosemary.
Pour water and lemon juice into skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until fish is firm, about 8 minutes.
Arrange asparagus on fish skillet.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are crisp, about 6 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas (2)
directions: Cut chicken breast into strips.
Soak in lemon lime and soy sauce for 3/4 hr.
Fry chicken with juice till done.
Add vegetables and saute for a few min.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix everything together and boil 1 hour.

title: mezetti
directions: Saute bell peppers, onion and celery in butter.
Brown ground beef.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together, sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly jelled.
Fold in whipped cream, oranges, marshmallows, coconut and grapes or fruit cocktail.
Mold.

title: chicken ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts with mixer.
Roll mixture in nuts.
Can be frozen.

title: graham bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix in 3-quart bowl all the ingredients.
Spread mixture in a well-greased 9-inch square pan. Bake about 35 minutes or until cake pulls from sides of pan. Cool.
Cut into 18 bars.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grate rind from lemon.
Set aside.
Squeeze juice from lemon. Mix juice with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.

title: chicken apple pot pie(also good with turkey)
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Mix with remaining ingredients and put in an oiled casserole or loaf dish.
Top with crust.
Cut vent holes in crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter in skillet until tender.
Add mushrooms and crushed rosemary.
Cook until liquid is gone.
Add cooked rice.
Reduce heat to low; cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in drained, chopped spinach, soup and cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients. Spread on party bread.

title: pear carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt and soda; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in pear, carrot and raisins.
Combine molasses and water; add to flour mixture mixing just to blend. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 9 servings.
Can be frozen for up to six weeks.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems, leaving caps intact.
Finely mince stems and saute in butter.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley and onion.
When mushroom stems are lightly browned, add them to stuffing mix and mix thoroughly.
Pile mix into mushroom caps and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix well pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: kay's favorite italian beef
directions: Cook roast in water.
(I cook mine in crock-pot all day.) Let cool and slice or chop it.
In saucepan add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over meat and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(I put sliced meat back in crock-pot and pour boiling broth over it and let it stay on low until ready to serve.)

title: divinity
directions: When syrup is at hard-ball stage, pour syrup in mixture slowly, beating egg white all the while.
I use a hand mixer. Continue beating until the shine is gone and mixture drips from the mixer blades in a small ribbon.
Immediately pour in chopped nuts mixing well with a spoon.
You can pour in a pan buttered or pan spreading immediately.
You can also drop by spoonfuls onto a sheet of waxed paper sprayed with Pam.
It helps if you have someone to pour the syrup while you beat.

title: black olive cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, then roll in chopped nuts.
Makes 2 cheese balls.
Great for freezing.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in a medium skillet.
Cook and stir green pepper in oil until crisp-tender.
Remove and keep warm.
Add steak strips to skillet.
Cook and stir until brown.
Add browned steak strips to green pepper.
Keep warm.
Mix water and cornstarch together; set aside.
Stir broth, soy sauce, sherry, garlic and ginger into drippings in skillet.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in green pepper and steak.
Serve over rice, if preferred.

title: pasta with artichokes and basil
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Stir artichokes, peppers, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in tomato and basil until heated through.
Add mixture to pasta; toss gently to mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook covered in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Then, cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie crusts and top with chopped peanuts.
Freeze for 8 hours.
Remove to fridge 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Break beef up slightly and saute.
Drain away fat.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring 4 cups water and 1 tablespoon salt to boil in large kettle.
Add noodles and bring to full boil.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Put 1/2 the noodles in shallow baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients (except meat) and pour over noodles.
Add other 1/2 of noodles and pour meat mixture on top.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix french vanilla, pudding, vanilla pudding, sugar, milk cream cheese, and whipped topping together in large bowl.
Crumble oreos. Mix with other ingredients.
Place pudding mixture in a 9 x 11 glass dish.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and other 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and invert onto plates.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
If cake is not served immediately, pieces can also be warmed in a microwave.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese with salsa sauce in microwave, stirring occasionally.
Add beef and mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: instant miracle rolls(yield: 5 dozen)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and water with yeast and mix.
Place desired amount of dough on a floured cloth.
Pat out.
Cut with cutter.
Let warm to room temperature before baking in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Steam chicken about 1 hour; cool and remove bones and skin. Retain broth.
Use a nonstick spray on a skillet.
Add soy sauce and mushrooms and saute, covered, until tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in chicken broth; bring to a boil and thicken.
Add salsa and mushrooms to broth and simmer 15 minutes.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, make 2 layers each:
tortillas, chicken, cheese and sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: coconut cherry drops
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg and almond extract. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in maraschino cherries, coconut and pecans.
Drop by level tablespoons onto greased baking sheet. Top each cookie with a half maraschino cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/4's.
Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Mix sugar and cinnamon into a large Ziploc bag.
Shake biscuit 1/4's in Ziploc bag.
Line Bundt pan.
Add a layer of pecans, layer of biscuit 1/4's and layer of pecans.
Melt 1 stick butter and light brown sugar; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: tuna summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni to package directions, drain.
In large bowl combine macaroni, tuna, tomatoes, green peppers, green onions and parsley.
In a small bowl blend remaining ingredients.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Toss gently to mix.
Cover; chill thoroughly. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat the eggs slightly in a mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients except for half the cheese.
Mix well and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: grandma's caramel icing
directions: Combine sugars and cream in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil to soft ball stage, 234° on a candy thermometer, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add salt and vanilla. Cool for awhile (10 minutes), then beat until thick.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg substitute, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup applesauce, onion, 1 teaspoon mustard, celery, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into a round loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Add approximately 1/2 inch of water. Combine in remaining applesauce and 1 teaspoon mustard; stir in brown sugar, vinegar and allspice.
Make a depression in the top of the loaf and spoon mixture into the depression.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: deep-fried tiny squid(calamaretti fritti)
directions: Clean the squid, cutting the bodies into rings and the tentacles in half.
Dredge all the pieces by shaking them in a sturdy bag with the flour.
Bring the frying oil to a high heat (375°).
Drop the fish in a few at a time, so that the pan is full but not overcrowded.
Keep turning the pieces as they become golden and remove them with a slotted spoon when they are really crisp and thoroughly golden.
Drain on paper towels on a cookie sheet and sprinkle with salt.
Serve on a hot platter with the lemon wedges.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press in buttered cake pan.
Beat next 3 ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Add Velveeta.
Melt margarine; add flour to make a smooth paste.
Add paste to boiling mixture to thicken.
Add picante sauce, chili (optional) and lemon juice.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
When partially set, add pineapple, marshmallows, bananas and nuts.
In saucepan, cook juice, flour, sugar and egg.
When custard is cool, add whipped cream.
Spread custard mixture on top of jello.
Garnish with grated cheese.

title: picnic beans
directions: Brown onion and add remaining ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a large, well-greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all in food processor.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Make into small balls.
Roll into additional confectioners sugar.
Store in tightly closed plastic bag or covered container.
They may be rolled into confectioners sugar again after storage (if desired).
Very good.

title: tortilla crunch chicken fingers
directions: In medium bowl, combine fiesta herb with red pepper soup mix and tortilla chips.
In large plastic bag or another bowl, combine chicken and egg beaten with water, coating well.
Dip chicken in tortilla mixture, coating well.
In 15 1/2x10 1/2x1 jelly roll pan sprayed with cooking spray, arrange chicken; drizzle with margarine.

title: barbecue sauce no. 3
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler 1
directions: Melt butter and pour in pan.
Mix milk, sugar and flour in a bowl.
Stir with a spoon until all ingredients are mixed well. Pour into pan on top of butter.
Then pour can of peaches with juice evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix as you do any other cake.
Bake in slow oven (250 to 300°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend butter into corn syrup; stir in peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Turn candy onto pastry board; knead with hands until blended and smooth.
Add nuts gradually, pressing and kneading into dough. Press candy into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill for 1 hour; cut into squares.
Yield:
2 pounds.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix well ground beef, egg, onion, sauces and oatmeal or bread crumbs.
Roll into small balls.
Brown lightly in small amount of oil.
Mix and melt chili sauce and grape jelly.
Add meat balls and simmer together for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a crock-pot. Serve hot.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in hot fat until soft.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Dilute soup with milk or broth and add green chilies, onion and chicken (bite size pieces).
Simmer together for a few minutes.
Spoon some sauce over bottom of large casserole dish. Alternate layers of tortillas, cheese, onion, chili and chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.

title: pineapple and nut cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix this by hand.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool cake.
Spread on Cream Cheese Icing.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple. Add remaining ingredients. Chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and cocoa until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour until well mixed. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread Marshmallow Creme on top of cake, then ice.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon; flake salmon with a fork. Saute onion in margarine until tender; remove from heat and stir in salmon and everything else but the oil.
Form into 1 x 1 x 2 1/2-inch croquettes or small balls.
Coat with additional flour and deep fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain.

title: chile-cheese tomatoes
directions: Cut each large tomato into 3 thick slices.
Squeeze each gently to remove some of the seeds.
Arrange the tomatoes, with cut sides up, on the rack of a broiler pan.
In a small bowl, combine the sour cream with the salt, pepper, sugar, flour, green onion and green chilies; stir until well blended.
Spoon mixture evenly over the tomatoes, then sprinkle the cheese evenly over the top.
Just before serving, place tomatoes in a preheated broiler about 4 inches from heat; broil just until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown, about 4 minutes.
The tomatoes will be just warm.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: pungent pasta for two(spicy)
directions: I use a Teflon coated skillet (medium size).

title: gourmet dog treats
directions: Mix all the ingredients together to form a dough. Dust hands with flour and roll into desired shape. Place on greased cookie sheet; bake in an oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until crisp and brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions.
When slightly thickened, add cottage cheese, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Chill until stiff.
Mix diced apples with other sectioned or sliced fruits, coconut and marshmallows, then add the fruit mixture to the gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all.
Pour in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust of pie pastry and fit into 9-inch pie plate.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pastry-lined plate. Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes, add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour cooled syrup over crackers, dot gently with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges together. Cut slits in top crust to let steam escape or do a lattice top crust.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until crust is crisp and golden.
Serve warm.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add vinegar and beet liquid. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add beets and butter.
Heat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit punch for a crowd
directions: Dissolve gelatins in 12 cups boiling water; cool.
Add juices and sugar.
Mix well, chill and serve.
Different flavors of gelatin and juices may be substituted for variety and color.
This punch may be frozen in gallon jars, allowing 6 to 8 hours to thaw before serving.
If frozen, no ice is needed.
Serves 75.

title: lovely lemon cheesecake(diabetic; low-fat)
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle side with half of the graham cracker crumbs.
Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container.
Add cottage cheese and cream cheese product; cover.
Blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes or until mixture is completely smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan; smooth top.
Sprinkle the remaining crumbs around outside edge.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
When ready to serve, remove side of spring-form pan.
Top cheesecake with pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.
(Calories 160; fat 7 grams; cholesterol 15 mg; diabetic exchange per serving:
1 whole milk and 1/2 fruit.)

title: mushroom business
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; drain.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper.
Grease an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Toast bread and paint with melted butter; cut into squares.
Put in pan and put mushroom mixture, mashed up celery, bell pepper and onion on top of bread. Add salt and pepper; add another layer of bread.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cover with mushroom soup, layer of bread and Swiss cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar.
Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut, nuts and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Don't open oven until done, it will fall!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables with cheese and mayonnaise; season with salt and pepper.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix crackers with margarine and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marvelous mashed potatoes(microwave)
directions: Microwave
potatoes
in
rectangular
microwavable dish (large) as directed on package.
Whip potatoes, smooth top and spread
with
sour	cream.	Sprinkle
with	cheese,
bacon and onions.
Microwave,
uncovered, on High for approximately 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour ham cubes
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and bouillon.
Drain pineapple chunks; reserve syrup.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple syrup, water, honey, vinegar and soy sauce to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks, ham cubes and olives.
Keep hot for serving.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Combine potatoes and water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cook, covered 12 to 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Drain, reserving liquid.
Mash the potatoes; set aside.

Place potato liquid in a large bowl. Add milk. Cool to lukewarm (110° to 115°). Dissolve yeast in liquid. Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and mashed potatoes. With a spoon, stir in 2 cups of the flour at a time, mixing well after each addition, using 5 cups of the flour. Turn out on a lightly floured surface. Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes). Shape dough in a large ball. Place in greased bowl. Cover and chill overnight. Grease three 9-inch round baking pans.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: greek green beans
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; add onion and cinnamon. Cook, stirring often, 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add green beans, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato paste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Simmer pumpkin, sweet potatoes, onions and hot pepper pods in very little water. Let simmer until the onions are soft and the pumpkin is soft enough to mash. Remove the pepper pod from its shell. Add spices. Add butter. Add condensed milk and salt to taste.

title: chicken biskette casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Add water (or soy sauce), chicken broth, 1/4 cup flour, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook approximately 3 minutes, until thickened. Add frozen vegetables and chicken.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining flour, oatmeal and baking powder.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in milk and egg white until moist. Drop by tablespoon onto top of chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until golden.

title: marshmallow-rice krispies ball
directions: Mix caramels and milk.
Microwave.
Use kitchen tongs to dip marshmallows into the caramel/milk mixture, then roll in Rice Krispies.
Place on a rack to cool.
These are very delicious and make a light dessert.

title: easy chocolate chewies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl, stirring until smooth.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: wassail
directions: Boil water, sugar
and	spices,
then let stand 1 hour. Mix remaining
items to above mixture.	Store in refrigerator. Keeps for weeks.	Serve hot.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash, dry and chill spinach. Tear into bite-size pieces and just before serving, prepare sauce. Dice bacon and fry until crisp. Reduce heat; add sugar, green onions, salt to taste, vinegar and dry mustard. Bring to a boil; remove from heat and pour over spinach. Toss lightly.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix nuts and coconut together.
Stir half of mixture into batter and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle remainder of mixture over filling. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.)
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except hot dogs) and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Then top with hot dogs and bake until they are golden brown.

title: chocolate-nut-pretzels
directions: Have
pretzels and nuts ready before melting chocolate. Melt over very
low
heat.
Mix all together and spread on wax paper very thinly.
Let
set
to	cool.
Break up and store in tight container with layer of wax paper in between.

title: one-step ham casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, mushrooms and dried onion.
Add ham, uncooked macaroni, pimento and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven about 50 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Uncover; sprinkle cheese on top. Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Cook and cool pie crusts.
Brown coconut in butter.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk with mixer.
Layer browned coconut, pecans, caramel topping and cream cheese mixture.
Then repeat layers.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with caramel topping. Freeze.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Mix oil and seasoning well.
Pour over pretzels, coating well.
Drain on paper towels; pack in airtight container.

title: braised short ribs with vegetables
directions: Brown short ribs, coated with flour, in large skillet with oil.
Place vegetables in crock-pot; add short ribs.
Combine spices and beef broth.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove short ribs and vegetables.
Turn control to high.
Dissolve 1/2 cup flour into small amount of water.
Stir into sauce and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes, until thickened. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar with beater.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon into a 9-inch, floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool before turning out onto wire rack to cool.
Makes one 9-inch tube cake.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and bake in sheet cake pan.
Cook vanilla pudding according to directions on package and cool.

title: cucumber sour cream salad
directions: Blend together sugar, salt, sour cream, onion and vinegar in bowl.
Add cucumbers and mix well.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus spears and water chestnuts, saving 1 1/2 cups of the combined liquids. Mix the flour and milk until smooth. Add to reserved liquid with butter, cheese and seasonings; cook on medium heat until thick and add pimento. Arrange asparagus in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place water chestnuts over asparagus; top with sliced eggs. Pour sauce evenly over all and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Melt marshmallows with milk; stir until smooth.
Chill until thickened.
Combine softened cream cheese and vanilla, beating until well blended and fluffy.
Whip in the marshmallow mixture; fold in Dream Whip which has been whipped.
Pour half of mixture into crust.
Cover with pie filling; top with remaining cheesecake mixture.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop all ingredients; mix all together.
Mix dressing with salad and let set overnight.

title: dad's famous "man sized casserole"
directions: Melt shortening in a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over low heat until onion is transparent.
Add ground beef.
Cook over medium heat until lightly browned, stirring with a fork to break up meat.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: hamburger-rotel and cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
In another saucepan, heat tomatoes and add cheese, sliced.
Melt cheese thoroughly and add hamburger meat.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook brown sugar, Pet milk, white sugar and salt to a soft ball stage (about 30 minutes).
Take off fire and add Karo syrup, butter and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to firm a little and then fold in pecans.
Drop with a spoon onto greased wax paper.

title: noodle dish
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add bell pepper, onion, seasonings, etc. Add sauce and mushrooms.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Cut cheese in chunks and let melt (all must be melted). Add cooked noodles and mix together in casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix and bring to simmer first three ingredients.
Stir and let simmer again.
Remove from heat.
Pour off juice and save, after cooling a few minutes.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Mix gelatin and cake mix.
In separate bowl, beat eggs with oil, nectar and flavoring.
Add to dry mixture. Mix well and pour in steeple pan.
Bake in slow oven for one hour at 325°.
While still hot, poke holes in cake and pour over cake a mixture of one cup powdered sugar combined with four tablespoons of lemon juice. Cool in pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together; put in baking
pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top (as desired).
Bake at 300°
for
30	minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Use 1 cup Cool Whip add 1 tablespoon grated orange peel and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg. Mix well and spread generously on pie and serve.

title: tomato dumplins
directions: Mix flour and water in a bowl.
Mix like biscuit dough.
Add the egg.
Put tomatoes and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Drop dough mixture into pan using a teaspoon. Cook until dumplins are done.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt oleo and work in the flour to make a dough.
Press into pizza pan and add nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool completely.

title: festive strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water; add 2 cups cold water. Add strawberries and pecans and stir.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into mold or other appropriate dish in refrigerator until congealed.
Let remaining mixture thicken in refrigerator, but not congeal.
Spread sour cream on congealed mixture in mold.
Pour remaining thickened gelatin mixture over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: baklava
directions: Brush a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan with melted butter.
Fold a sheet of filo in half and carefully lay in pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Repeat for 6 layers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Repeat until all ingredients are used and end with a pastry layer, brushed with butter.
Cut in diamond shapes, 2-inches wide.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 minutes longer.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle paprika on steak and brown in butter.
Add 1 can beef broth and garlic powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add green onions and peppers.
Combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Add to steak.
Stir until soup thickens.
Take off heat.
Add tomatoes that have been quartered.
Serve over cooked rice.
Cook rice as directed on box for minute rice.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and 1/3 c. sugar, mixing until blended.
Add egg; mix well. Combine margarine, water and chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Stir into the combined flour & 2 c. sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, baking soda & salt.
Pour into greased & floured large baking pan.

title: spicy tomato sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: raisin-cinnamon doughnut
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter or 2 knives.
Mixture should look like small bowls. Stir in milk and raisins.
Turn onto a lightly floured board. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with floured doughnut cutter.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf in a shallow pan.
Place 1/2 cup of water in the pan and top with loaf with 2 strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttery onion pretzels
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Stir in soup mix.
Heat and stir until well mixed.
Add pretzels.
Toss to coat.
Spread pretzel mixture in a baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 6 cups.

title: beef and rice skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat quickly in oil, leaving meat in coarse chunks. Drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add seasoning, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring to a boil and stir in rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Serves 4.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Makes 2 pies.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix together.
Roll in lengths with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Remove wrap; bake on broiler pan for 1 hour at 300°. Pat excess fat with paper towel while warm.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Separate egg and beat egg white stiff.
To sifted dry ingredients, add oil, buttermilk and egg yolk.
Beat until well mixed.
More buttermilk may be added, if desired.
Fold in egg white.
Cook on hot griddle at 400° until bubbles form.
Turn over; cook until done.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim all fat from pork chops. Beat egg whites with evaporated skim milk. Place chops in milk mixture. Let stand for 5 minutes, turning chops once.

title: easy everything cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oatmeal and chocolate chips, in a large mixer bowl until well blended.
Add oatmeal and chips, mixing by hand, until blended.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: roman summer sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes and pasta, and simmer.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Cook pasta and drain.
Add sauce and heat for a minute or two.
Serve with grated cheese and crushed pepper.

title: coconut oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Then add coconut and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients. Pour into ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: japanese pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy dream icing
directions: Beat all ingredients together until thickened.
Spread on cake.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put cranberry sauce in a small bowl and break up with wire whisk.
Add to jello and mix in with wire whisk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
When partially thickened, put in mold or a 9 x 11-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: cheese grits
directions: Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 15 people.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets separately until tender (do not overcook). Peel and put beets into glass jars.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, celery seed, and mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Apply boiling vinegar mixture to beets and seal.
Do not process.

title: 7 ingredient salad
directions: Mix onion, mayo, peas and sugar. Place mixture on top of lettuce. Top with cheese and bacon bits.

title: pineapple-orange sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, applesauce, eggs and syrup from Mandarin oranges for 2 minutes by hand.
Then fold in one can of Mandarin oranges.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 2 and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter and flour; add to the corn.
Mix well and remove from heat.
Serves 8.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil water and sugar together until sugar dissolves.
Add coffee, orange juice and lemonade.
Remove from heat, mix until dissolved and add brandy.
Stir well.
Put in large container and freeze at least 7 to 8 hours before serving.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat 2 egg whites and dash of salt until stiff.
Fold in 1 cup sugar.
Pour in pecans and mix well.
Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecan mixture in butter and bake in 325° oven for about 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in pan. Put into 2-quart casserole. Add soup. Top with potatoes. Dot with butter, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour filling into pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Drizzle margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered with foil.
Remove foil and cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sparkling citrus punch
directions: Mix lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice in a gallon jug. Finish filling jug with water. Chill.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Melt butter with garlic. Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces into butter. Coat pieces with crumb mixture. Place in 15 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.

Tuck sides of chicken under to form rolls. Be sure sides of rolls do not touch each other. Pour remainder of butter over chicken rolls. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Baste occasionally with pan juices.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat of liquid.
Combine other ingredients in a shallow pie plate that has been greased with butter.
Carefully fold in crab meat.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is bubbly and brown.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt the first 2 ingredients in top of double boiler; cool a little and add a beaten egg.
Measure 3 good cups of colored miniature marshmallows in bowl (if large is all that you can get, cut them and mix with chocolate mixture).
Spread coconut over waxed paper; spread mixture over it and roll.
Then I put foil firm around that and press firm.
Chill quite awhile and cut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and water.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and syrup; mix well.
Stir baking soda into oats.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 80 cookies!

title: refrigerator pineapple cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press onto the bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water and cool to lukewarm.
In a blender, thoroughly mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Slowly add the gelatin and blend well.
Pour the mixture into the chilled crust and refrigerate until firm.
In a saucepan, bring the crushed pineapple with juice, the water and cornstarch to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool 15 minutes and spread over the top of the cheese cake.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 16 servings at 125 calories per serving.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: In a large skillet, combine chicken and about 1/3 bottle of Italian dressing.
Saute until the chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover; simmer for 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with cheese.
This makes 5 generous servings.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, water, apple cider, cinnamon candies and cloves; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add apples slices; cook, turning occasionally, until apples are just tender, about 6 to 8 minutes. Spoon apples and liquid into jars; cover and refrigerate overnight for flavors to blend.
Yields 5 pints.

title: norwegian lefsa
directions: Blend potatoes and shortening. Allow to cool in refrigerator. With 5 cups of potato mix, blend in cream, salt, sugar and flour. Take a 1/4 portion and roll out on a floured surface.
This dough is very difficult to handle, so work with small amount at a time. Too much flour makes the Lefsa tough.
Cook on a flat plate or pan.

title: cheese wafers
directions: In a mixer, combine butter and grated cheese.
Sift flour, salt and red pepper together.
Add to cheese mixture and blend.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix. Dough will be stiff.
Make a ball from approximately 1 teaspoon dough.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and press flat with a fork to look like a round wafer. Should fill 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until well done but not real brown.

title: beef potato casserole
directions: In greased baking
dish,
layer
vegetables
and
meat. Pour liquid, salt and
pepper
over
the casserole.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.	Uncover the last 1/2 hour so liquid will thicken.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marcia's mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion in garlic salt, pepper and butter for about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and burgundy wine.
Cook at low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Longer they are cooked the better they are.)
Mix corn starch in small bowl with 1 tablespoon water.
Add to mushrooms. Cook 5 more minutes.
Can be cooked a day in advance.
Decrease or increase corn starch for thickness.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first five ingredients thoroughly.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into
pie shell and bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 minutes longer. Yields 6 servings.

title: easy does it doughnuts
directions: Stir together; drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Roll in sugar or glaze.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: clam pie
directions: In a medium skillet, fry bacon until browned and crisp. Remove; drain on paper and crumble.
Pour off bacon drippings from the skillet; add butter.
Add onion; cook until golden (5 minutes).
Stir in celery and potatoes; cover.
Cook until softened (5 minutes).
Put in baking dish with drained clams and bacon.
Make a white sauce, adding some of the clam juice.
